65/*!
66 * For type 3 negative cache entries, we will remember that the address is
67 * broken for this long. XXXMLG This is also used for actual addresses, too.
68 * The intent is to keep us from constantly asking about A/AAAA records
69 * if the zone has extremely low TTLs.
70 */
71#define ADB_CACHE_MINIMUM 10 /*%< seconds */
72#define ADB_CACHE_MAXIMUM 86400 /*%< seconds (86400 = 24 hours) */
73#define ADB_ENTRY_WINDOW 1800 /*%< seconds */
74
75/*%
76 * The period in seconds after which an ADB name entry is regarded as stale
77 * and forced to be cleaned up.
78 * TODO: This should probably be configurable at run-time.
79 */
80#ifndef ADB_STALE_MARGIN
81#define ADB_STALE_MARGIN 1800
82#endif

99/*% dns adb structure */
100struct dns_adb {
101 unsigned int magic;
102
103 isc_mutex_t lock;
104 isc_mutex_t reflock; /*%< Covers irefcnt, erefcnt */
105 isc_mutex_t overmemlock; /*%< Covers overmem */
106 isc_mem_t *mctx;
107 dns_view_t *view;
108
109 isc_taskmgr_t *taskmgr;
110 isc_task_t *task;
111 isc_task_t *excl;
112
113 isc_interval_t tick_interval;
114 int next_cleanbucket;
115
116 unsigned int irefcnt;
117 unsigned int erefcnt;
118
119 isc_mutex_t mplock;
120 isc_mempool_t *nmp; /*%< dns_adbname_t */
121 isc_mempool_t *nhmp; /*%< dns_adbnamehook_t */
122 isc_mempool_t *limp; /*%< dns_adblameinfo_t */
123 isc_mempool_t *emp; /*%< dns_adbentry_t */
124 isc_mempool_t *ahmp; /*%< dns_adbfind_t */
125 isc_mempool_t *aimp; /*%< dns_adbaddrinfo_t */
126 isc_mempool_t *afmp; /*%< dns_adbfetch_t */
127
128 /*!
129 * Bucketized locks and lists for names.
130 *
131 * XXXRTH Have a per-bucket structure that contains all of these?
132 */
133 unsigned int nnames;
134 isc_mutex_t namescntlock;
135 unsigned int namescnt;
136 dns_adbnamelist_t *names;
137 dns_adbnamelist_t *deadnames;
138 isc_mutex_t *namelocks;
139 bool *name_sd;
140 unsigned int *name_refcnt;
141
142 /*!
143 * Bucketized locks and lists for entries.
144 *
145 * XXXRTH Have a per-bucket structure that contains all of these?
146 */
147 unsigned int nentries;
148 isc_mutex_t entriescntlock;
149 unsigned int entriescnt;
150 dns_adbentrylist_t *entries;
151 dns_adbentrylist_t *deadentries;
152 isc_mutex_t *entrylocks;
153 bool *entry_sd; /*%< shutting down */
154 unsigned int *entry_refcnt;
155
156 isc_event_t cevent;
157 bool cevent_out;
158 bool shutting_down;
159 isc_eventlist_t whenshutdown;
160 isc_event_t growentries;
161 bool growentries_sent;
162 isc_event_t grownames;
163 bool grownames_sent;
164
165 uint32_t quota;
166 uint32_t atr_freq;
167 double atr_low;
168 double atr_high;
169 double atr_discount;
170};

210/*%
211 * This is a small widget that dangles off a dns_adbname_t. It contains a
212 * pointer to the address information about this host, and a link to the next
213 * namehook that will contain the next address this host has.
214 */
215struct dns_adbnamehook {
216 unsigned int magic;
217 dns_adbentry_t *entry;
218 ISC_LINK(dns_adbnamehook_t) plink;
219};
220
221/*%
222 * This is a small widget that holds qname-specific information about an
223 * address. Currently limited to lameness, but could just as easily be
224 * extended to other types of information about zones.
225 */
226struct dns_adblameinfo {
227 unsigned int magic;
228
229 dns_name_t qname;
230 dns_rdatatype_t qtype;
231 isc_stdtime_t lame_timer;
232
233 ISC_LINK(dns_adblameinfo_t) plink;
234};
235
236/*%
237 * An address entry. It holds quite a bit of information about addresses,
238 * including edns state (in "flags"), rtt, and of course the address of
239 * the host.
240 */
241struct dns_adbentry {
242 unsigned int magic;
243
244 int lock_bucket;
245 unsigned int refcnt;
246 unsigned int nh;
247
248 unsigned int flags;
249 unsigned int srtt;
250 uint16_t udpsize;
251 unsigned int completed;
252 unsigned int timeouts;
253 unsigned char plain;
254 unsigned char plainto;
255 unsigned char edns;
256 unsigned char to4096; /* Our max. */
257
258 uint8_t mode;
259 uint32_t quota;
260 uint32_t active;
261 double atr;
262
263 /*
264 * Allow for encapsulated IPv4/IPv6 UDP packet over ethernet.
265 * Ethernet 1500 - IP(20) - IP6(40) - UDP(8) = 1432.
266 */
267 unsigned char to1432; /* Ethernet */
268 unsigned char to1232; /* IPv6 nofrag */
269 unsigned char to512; /* plain DNS */
270 isc_sockaddr_t sockaddr;
271 unsigned char * cookie;
272 uint16_t cookielen;
273
274 isc_stdtime_t expires;
275 isc_stdtime_t lastage;
276 /*%<
277 * A nonzero 'expires' field indicates that the entry should
278 * persist until that time. This allows entries found
279 * using dns_adb_findaddrinfo() to persist for a limited time
280 * even though they are not necessarily associated with a
281 * name.
282 */
283
284 ISC_LIST(dns_adblameinfo_t) lameinfo;
285 ISC_LINK(dns_adbentry_t) plink;
286};

361/*
362 * MUST NOT overlap DNS_ADBFIND_* flags!
363 */
364#define FIND_EVENT_SENT 0x40000000
365#define FIND_EVENT_FREED 0x80000000
366#define FIND_EVENTSENT(h) (((h)->flags & FIND_EVENT_SENT) != 0)
367#define FIND_EVENTFREED(h) (((h)->flags & FIND_EVENT_FREED) != 0)
368
369#define NAME_NEEDS_POKE 0x80000000
370#define NAME_IS_DEAD 0x40000000
371#define NAME_HINT_OK DNS_ADBFIND_HINTOK
372#define NAME_GLUE_OK DNS_ADBFIND_GLUEOK
373#define NAME_STARTATZONE DNS_ADBFIND_STARTATZONE
374#define NAME_DEAD(n) (((n)->flags & NAME_IS_DEAD) != 0)
375#define NAME_NEEDSPOKE(n) (((n)->flags & NAME_NEEDS_POKE) != 0)
376#define NAME_GLUEOK(n) (((n)->flags & NAME_GLUE_OK) != 0)
377#define NAME_HINTOK(n) (((n)->flags & NAME_HINT_OK) != 0)
378
379/*
380 * Private flag(s) for entries.
381 * MUST NOT overlap FCTX_ADDRINFO_xxx and DNS_FETCHOPT_NOEDNS0.
382 */
383#define ENTRY_IS_DEAD 0x00400000
384
385/*
386 * To the name, address classes are all that really exist. If it has a
387 * V6 address it doesn't care if it came from a AAAA query.
388 */
389#define NAME_HAS_V4(n) (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY((n)->v4))
390#define NAME_HAS_V6(n) (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY((n)->v6))
391#define NAME_HAS_ADDRS(n) (NAME_HAS_V4(n) || NAME_HAS_V6(n))
392
393/*
394 * Fetches are broken out into A and AAAA types. In some cases,
395 * however, it makes more sense to test for a particular class of fetches,
396 * like V4 or V6 above.
397 * Note: since we have removed the support of A6 in adb, FETCH_A and FETCH_AAAA
398 * are now equal to FETCH_V4 and FETCH_V6, respectively.
399 */
400#define NAME_FETCH_A(n) ((n)->fetch_a != NULL)
401#define NAME_FETCH_AAAA(n) ((n)->fetch_aaaa != NULL)
402#define NAME_FETCH_V4(n) (NAME_FETCH_A(n))
403#define NAME_FETCH_V6(n) (NAME_FETCH_AAAA(n))
404#define NAME_FETCH(n) (NAME_FETCH_V4(n) || NAME_FETCH_V6(n))
405
406/*
407 * Find options and tests to see if there are addresses on the list.
408 */
409#define FIND_WANTEVENT(fn) (((fn)->options & DNS_ADBFIND_WANTEVENT) != 0)
410#define FIND_WANTEMPTYEVENT(fn) (((fn)->options & DNS_ADBFIND_EMPTYEVENT) != 0)
411#define FIND_AVOIDFETCHES(fn) (((fn)->options & DNS_ADBFIND_AVOIDFETCHES) \
412 != 0)
413#define FIND_STARTATZONE(fn) (((fn)->options & DNS_ADBFIND_STARTATZONE) \
414 != 0)
415#define FIND_HINTOK(fn) (((fn)->options & DNS_ADBFIND_HINTOK) != 0)
416#define FIND_GLUEOK(fn) (((fn)->options & DNS_ADBFIND_GLUEOK) != 0)
417#define FIND_HAS_ADDRS(fn) (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY((fn)->list))
418#define FIND_RETURNLAME(fn) (((fn)->options & DNS_ADBFIND_RETURNLAME) != 0)
419
420/*
421 * These are currently used on simple unsigned ints, so they are
422 * not really associated with any particular type.
423 */
424#define WANT_INET(x) (((x) & DNS_ADBFIND_INET) != 0)
425#define WANT_INET6(x) (((x) & DNS_ADBFIND_INET6) != 0)
426
427#define EXPIRE_OK(exp, now) ((exp == INT_MAX) || (exp < now))
428
429/*
430 * Find out if the flags on a name (nf) indicate if it is a hint or
431 * glue, and compare this to the appropriate bits set in o, to see if
432 * this is ok.
433 */
434#define GLUE_OK(nf, o) (!NAME_GLUEOK(nf) || (((o) & DNS_ADBFIND_GLUEOK) != 0))
435#define HINT_OK(nf, o) (!NAME_HINTOK(nf) || (((o) & DNS_ADBFIND_HINTOK) != 0))
436#define GLUEHINT_OK(nf, o) (GLUE_OK(nf, o) || HINT_OK(nf, o))
437#define STARTATZONE_MATCHES(nf, o) (((nf)->flags & NAME_STARTATZONE) == \
438 ((o) & DNS_ADBFIND_STARTATZONE))

535static inline dns_ttl_t
536ttlclamp(dns_ttl_t ttl) {
537 if (ttl < ADB_CACHE_MINIMUM)
538 ttl = ADB_CACHE_MINIMUM;
539 if (ttl > ADB_CACHE_MAXIMUM)
540 ttl = ADB_CACHE_MAXIMUM;
541
542 return (ttl);
543}

545/*
546 * Hashing is most efficient if the number of buckets is prime.
547 * The sequence below is the closest previous primes to 2^n and
548 * 1.5 * 2^n, for values of n from 10 to 28. (The tables will
549 * no longer grow beyond 2^28 entries.)
550 */
551static const unsigned nbuckets[] = { 1021, 1531, 2039, 3067, 4093, 6143,
552 8191, 12281, 16381, 24571, 32749,
553 49193, 65521, 98299, 131071, 199603,
554 262139, 393209, 524287, 768431, 1048573,
555 1572853, 2097143, 3145721, 4194301,
556 6291449, 8388593, 12582893, 16777213,
557 25165813, 33554393, 50331599, 67108859,
558 100663291, 134217689, 201326557,
559 268535431, 0 };

561static void
562grow_entries(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *ev) {
563 dns_adb_t *adb;
564 dns_adbentry_t *e;
565 dns_adbentrylist_t *newdeadentries = NULL;
566 dns_adbentrylist_t *newentries = NULL;
567 bool *newentry_sd = NULL;
568 isc_mutex_t *newentrylocks = NULL;
569 isc_result_t result;
570 unsigned int *newentry_refcnt = NULL;
571 unsigned int i, n, bucket;
572
573 adb = ev->ev_arg;
574 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
575
576 isc_event_free(&ev);
577
578 result = isc_task_beginexclusive(task);
579 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
580 goto check_exit;
581
582 i = 0;
583 while (nbuckets[i] != 0 && adb->nentries >= nbuckets[i])
584 i++;
585 if (nbuckets[i] != 0)
586 n = nbuckets[i];
587 else
588 goto done;
589
590 DP(ISC_LOG_INFO, "adb: grow_entries to %u starting", n);
591
592 /*
593 * Are we shutting down?
594 */
595 for (i = 0; i < adb->nentries; i++)
596 if (adb->entry_sd[i])
597 goto cleanup;
598
599 /*
600 * Grab all the resources we need.
601 */
602 newentries = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, sizeof(*newentries) * n);
603 newdeadentries = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, sizeof(*newdeadentries) * n);
604 newentrylocks = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, sizeof(*newentrylocks) * n);
605 newentry_sd = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, sizeof(*newentry_sd) * n);
606 newentry_refcnt = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, sizeof(*newentry_refcnt) * n);
607 if (newentries == NULL || newdeadentries == NULL ||
608 newentrylocks == NULL || newentry_sd == NULL ||
609 newentry_refcnt == NULL)
610 goto cleanup;
611
612 /*
613 * Initialise the new resources.
614 */
615 isc_mutexblock_init(newentrylocks, n);
616
617 for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
618 ISC_LIST_INIT(newentries[i]);
619 ISC_LIST_INIT(newdeadentries[i]);
620 newentry_sd[i] = false;
621 newentry_refcnt[i] = 0;
622 adb->irefcnt++;
623 }
624
625 /*
626 * Move entries to new arrays.
627 */
628 for (i = 0; i < adb->nentries; i++) {
629 e = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->entries[i]);
630 while (e != NULL) {
631 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->entries[i], e, plink);
632 bucket = isc_sockaddr_hash(&e->sockaddr, true) % n;
633 e->lock_bucket = bucket;
634 ISC_LIST_APPEND(newentries[bucket], e, plink);
635 INSIST(adb->entry_refcnt[i] > 0);
636 adb->entry_refcnt[i]--;
637 newentry_refcnt[bucket]++;
638 e = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->entries[i]);
639 }
640 e = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->deadentries[i]);
641 while (e != NULL) {
642 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->deadentries[i], e, plink);
643 bucket = isc_sockaddr_hash(&e->sockaddr, true) % n;
644 e->lock_bucket = bucket;
645 ISC_LIST_APPEND(newdeadentries[bucket], e, plink);
646 INSIST(adb->entry_refcnt[i] > 0);
647 adb->entry_refcnt[i]--;
648 newentry_refcnt[bucket]++;
649 e = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->deadentries[i]);
650 }
651 INSIST(adb->entry_refcnt[i] == 0);
652 adb->irefcnt--;
653 }
654
655 /*
656 * Cleanup old resources.
657 */
658 isc_mutexblock_destroy(adb->entrylocks, adb->nentries);
659 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entries,
660 sizeof(*adb->entries) * adb->nentries);
661 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->deadentries,
662 sizeof(*adb->deadentries) * adb->nentries);
663 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entrylocks,
664 sizeof(*adb->entrylocks) * adb->nentries);
665 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entry_sd,
666 sizeof(*adb->entry_sd) * adb->nentries);
667 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entry_refcnt,
668 sizeof(*adb->entry_refcnt) * adb->nentries);
669
670 /*
671 * Install new resources.
672 */
673 adb->entries = newentries;
674 adb->deadentries = newdeadentries;
675 adb->entrylocks = newentrylocks;
676 adb->entry_sd = newentry_sd;
677 adb->entry_refcnt = newentry_refcnt;
678 adb->nentries = n;
679
680 set_adbstat(adb, adb->nentries, dns_adbstats_nentries);
681
682 /*
683 * Only on success do we set adb->growentries_sent to false.
684 * This will prevent us being continuously being called on error.
685 */
686 adb->growentries_sent = false;
687 goto done;
688
689 cleanup:
690 if (newentries != NULL)
691 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, newentries,
692 sizeof(*newentries) * n);
693 if (newdeadentries != NULL)
694 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, newdeadentries,
695 sizeof(*newdeadentries) * n);
696 if (newentrylocks != NULL)
697 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, newentrylocks,
698 sizeof(*newentrylocks) * n);
699 if (newentry_sd != NULL)
700 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, newentry_sd,
701 sizeof(*newentry_sd) * n);
702 if (newentry_refcnt != NULL)
703 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, newentry_refcnt,
704 sizeof(*newentry_refcnt) * n);
705 done:
706 isc_task_endexclusive(task);
707
708 check_exit:
709 LOCK(&adb->lock);
710 if (dec_adb_irefcnt(adb))
711 check_exit(adb);
712 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
713 DP(ISC_LOG_INFO, "adb: grow_entries finished");
714}

716static void
717grow_names(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *ev) {
718 dns_adb_t *adb;
719 dns_adbname_t *name;
720 dns_adbnamelist_t *newdeadnames = NULL;
721 dns_adbnamelist_t *newnames = NULL;
722 bool *newname_sd = NULL;
723 isc_mutex_t *newnamelocks = NULL;
724 isc_result_t result;
725 unsigned int *newname_refcnt = NULL;
726 unsigned int i, n, bucket;
727
728 adb = ev->ev_arg;
729 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
730
731 isc_event_free(&ev);
732
733 result = isc_task_beginexclusive(task);
734 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
735 goto check_exit;
736
737 i = 0;
738 while (nbuckets[i] != 0 && adb->nnames >= nbuckets[i])
739 i++;
740 if (nbuckets[i] != 0)
741 n = nbuckets[i];
742 else
743 goto done;
744
745 DP(ISC_LOG_INFO, "adb: grow_names to %u starting", n);
746
747 /*
748 * Are we shutting down?
749 */
750 for (i = 0; i < adb->nnames; i++)
751 if (adb->name_sd[i])
752 goto cleanup;
753
754 /*
755 * Grab all the resources we need.
756 */
757 newnames = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, sizeof(*newnames) * n);
758 newdeadnames = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, sizeof(*newdeadnames) * n);
759 newnamelocks = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, sizeof(*newnamelocks) * n);
760 newname_sd = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, sizeof(*newname_sd) * n);
761 newname_refcnt = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, sizeof(*newname_refcnt) * n);
762 if (newnames == NULL || newdeadnames == NULL ||
763 newnamelocks == NULL || newname_sd == NULL ||
764 newname_refcnt == NULL)
765 goto cleanup;
766
767 /*
768 * Initialise the new resources.
769 */
770 isc_mutexblock_init(newnamelocks, n);
771
772 for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
773 ISC_LIST_INIT(newnames[i]);
774 ISC_LIST_INIT(newdeadnames[i]);
775 newname_sd[i] = false;
776 newname_refcnt[i] = 0;
777 adb->irefcnt++;
778 }
779
780 /*
781 * Move names to new arrays.
782 */
783 for (i = 0; i < adb->nnames; i++) {
784 name = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->names[i]);
785 while (name != NULL) {
786 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->names[i], name, plink);
787 bucket = dns_name_fullhash(&name->name, true) % n;
788 name->lock_bucket = bucket;
789 ISC_LIST_APPEND(newnames[bucket], name, plink);
790 INSIST(adb->name_refcnt[i] > 0);
791 adb->name_refcnt[i]--;
792 newname_refcnt[bucket]++;
793 name = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->names[i]);
794 }
795 name = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->deadnames[i]);
796 while (name != NULL) {
797 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->deadnames[i], name, plink);
798 bucket = dns_name_fullhash(&name->name, true) % n;
799 name->lock_bucket = bucket;
800 ISC_LIST_APPEND(newdeadnames[bucket], name, plink);
801 INSIST(adb->name_refcnt[i] > 0);
802 adb->name_refcnt[i]--;
803 newname_refcnt[bucket]++;
804 name = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->deadnames[i]);
805 }
806 INSIST(adb->name_refcnt[i] == 0);
807 adb->irefcnt--;
808 }
809
810 /*
811 * Cleanup old resources.
812 */
813 isc_mutexblock_destroy(adb->namelocks, adb->nnames);
814 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->names,
815 sizeof(*adb->names) * adb->nnames);
816 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->deadnames,
817 sizeof(*adb->deadnames) * adb->nnames);
818 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->namelocks,
819 sizeof(*adb->namelocks) * adb->nnames);
820 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->name_sd,
821 sizeof(*adb->name_sd) * adb->nnames);
822 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->name_refcnt,
823 sizeof(*adb->name_refcnt) * adb->nnames);
824
825 /*
826 * Install new resources.
827 */
828 adb->names = newnames;
829 adb->deadnames = newdeadnames;
830 adb->namelocks = newnamelocks;
831 adb->name_sd = newname_sd;
832 adb->name_refcnt = newname_refcnt;
833 adb->nnames = n;
834
835 set_adbstat(adb, adb->nnames, dns_adbstats_nnames);
836
837 /*
838 * Only on success do we set adb->grownames_sent to false.
839 * This will prevent us being continuously being called on error.
840 */
841 adb->grownames_sent = false;
842 goto done;
843
844 cleanup:
845 if (newnames != NULL)
846 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, newnames, sizeof(*newnames) * n);
847 if (newdeadnames != NULL)
848 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, newdeadnames, sizeof(*newdeadnames) * n);
849 if (newnamelocks != NULL)
850 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, newnamelocks, sizeof(*newnamelocks) * n);
851 if (newname_sd != NULL)
852 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, newname_sd, sizeof(*newname_sd) * n);
853 if (newname_refcnt != NULL)
854 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, newname_refcnt,
855 sizeof(*newname_refcnt) * n);
856 done:
857 isc_task_endexclusive(task);
858
859 check_exit:
860 LOCK(&adb->lock);
861 if (dec_adb_irefcnt(adb))
862 check_exit(adb);
863 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
864 DP(ISC_LOG_INFO, "adb: grow_names finished");
865}

867/*
868 * Requires the adbname bucket be locked and that no entry buckets be locked.
869 *
870 * This code handles A and AAAA rdatasets only.
871 */
872static isc_result_t
873import_rdataset(dns_adbname_t *adbname, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
874 isc_stdtime_t now)
875{
876 isc_result_t result;
877 dns_adb_t *adb;
878 dns_adbnamehook_t *nh;
879 dns_adbnamehook_t *anh;
880 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
881 struct in_addr ina;
882 struct in6_addr in6a;
883 isc_sockaddr_t sockaddr;
884 dns_adbentry_t *foundentry; /* NO CLEAN UP! */
885 int addr_bucket;
886 bool new_addresses_added;
887 dns_rdatatype_t rdtype;
888 unsigned int findoptions;
889 dns_adbnamehooklist_t *hookhead;
890
891 INSIST(DNS_ADBNAME_VALID(adbname));
892 adb = adbname->adb;
893 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
894
895 rdtype = rdataset->type;
896 INSIST((rdtype == dns_rdatatype_a) || (rdtype == dns_rdatatype_aaaa));
897 if (rdtype == dns_rdatatype_a)
898 findoptions = DNS_ADBFIND_INET;
899 else
900 findoptions = DNS_ADBFIND_INET6;
901
902 addr_bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
903 new_addresses_added = false;
904
905 nh = NULL;
906 result = dns_rdataset_first(rdataset);
907 while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
908 dns_rdata_reset(&rdata);
909 dns_rdataset_current(rdataset, &rdata);
910 if (rdtype == dns_rdatatype_a) {
911 INSIST(rdata.length == 4);
912 memmove(&ina.s_addr, rdata.data, 4);
913 isc_sockaddr_fromin(&sockaddr, &ina, 0);
914 hookhead = &adbname->v4;
915 } else {
916 INSIST(rdata.length == 16);
917 memmove(in6a.s6_addr, rdata.data, 16);
918 isc_sockaddr_fromin6(&sockaddr, &in6a, 0);
919 hookhead = &adbname->v6;
920 }
921
922 INSIST(nh == NULL);
923 nh = new_adbnamehook(adb, NULL);
924 if (nh == NULL) {
925 adbname->partial_result |= findoptions;
926 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
927 goto fail;
928 }
929
930 foundentry = find_entry_and_lock(adb, &sockaddr, &addr_bucket,
931 now);
932 if (foundentry == NULL) {
933 dns_adbentry_t *entry;
934
935 entry = new_adbentry(adb);
936 if (entry == NULL) {
937 adbname->partial_result |= findoptions;
938 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
939 goto fail;
940 }
941
942 entry->sockaddr = sockaddr;
943 entry->refcnt = 1;
944 entry->nh = 1;
945
946 nh->entry = entry;
947
948 link_entry(adb, addr_bucket, entry);
949 } else {
950 for (anh = ISC_LIST_HEAD(*hookhead);
951 anh != NULL;
952 anh = ISC_LIST_NEXT(anh, plink))
953 if (anh->entry == foundentry)
954 break;
955 if (anh == NULL) {
956 foundentry->refcnt++;
957 foundentry->nh++;
958 nh->entry = foundentry;
959 } else
960 free_adbnamehook(adb, &nh);
961 }
962
963 new_addresses_added = true;
964 if (nh != NULL)
965 ISC_LIST_APPEND(*hookhead, nh, plink);
966 nh = NULL;
967 result = dns_rdataset_next(rdataset);
968 }
969
970 fail:
971 if (nh != NULL)
972 free_adbnamehook(adb, &nh);
973
974 if (addr_bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET)
975 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[addr_bucket]);
976
977 if (rdataset->trust == dns_trust_glue ||
978 rdataset->trust == dns_trust_additional)
979 rdataset->ttl = ADB_CACHE_MINIMUM;
980 else if (rdataset->trust == dns_trust_ultimate)
981 rdataset->ttl = 0;
982 else
983 rdataset->ttl = ttlclamp(rdataset->ttl);
984
985 if (rdtype == dns_rdatatype_a) {
986 DP(NCACHE_LEVEL, "expire_v4 set to MIN(%u,%u) import_rdataset",
987 adbname->expire_v4, now + rdataset->ttl);
988 adbname->expire_v4 = ISC_MIN(adbname->expire_v4,
989 ISC_MIN(now + ADB_ENTRY_WINDOW,
990 now + rdataset->ttl));
991 } else {
992 DP(NCACHE_LEVEL, "expire_v6 set to MIN(%u,%u) import_rdataset",
993 adbname->expire_v6, now + rdataset->ttl);
994 adbname->expire_v6 = ISC_MIN(adbname->expire_v6,
995 ISC_MIN(now + ADB_ENTRY_WINDOW,
996 now + rdataset->ttl));
997 }
998
999 if (new_addresses_added) {
1000 /*
1001 * Lie a little here. This is more or less so code that cares
1002 * can find out if any new information was added or not.
1003 */
1004 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1005 }
1006
1007 return (result);
1008}

1010/*
1011 * Requires the name's bucket be locked.
1012 */
1013static bool
1014kill_name(dns_adbname_t **n, isc_eventtype_t ev) {
1015 dns_adbname_t *name;
1016 bool result = false;
1017 bool result4, result6;
1018 int bucket;
1019 dns_adb_t *adb;
1020
1021 INSIST(n != NULL);
1022 name = *n;
1023 *n = NULL;
1024 INSIST(DNS_ADBNAME_VALID(name));
1025 adb = name->adb;
1026 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
1027
1028 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "killing name %p", name);
1029
1030 /*
1031 * If we're dead already, just check to see if we should go
1032 * away now or not.
1033 */
1034 if (NAME_DEAD(name) && !NAME_FETCH(name)) {
1035 result = unlink_name(adb, name);
1036 free_adbname(adb, &name);
1037 if (result)
1038 result = dec_adb_irefcnt(adb);
1039 return (result);
1040 }
1041
1042 /*
1043 * Clean up the name's various lists. These two are destructive
1044 * in that they will always empty the list.
1045 */
1046 clean_finds_at_name(name, ev, DNS_ADBFIND_ADDRESSMASK);
1047 result4 = clean_namehooks(adb, &name->v4);
1048 result6 = clean_namehooks(adb, &name->v6);
1049 clean_target(adb, &name->target);
1050 result = (result4 || result6);
1051
1052 /*
1053 * If fetches are running, cancel them. If none are running, we can
1054 * just kill the name here.
1055 */
1056 if (!NAME_FETCH(name)) {
1057 INSIST(result == false);
1058 result = unlink_name(adb, name);
1059 free_adbname(adb, &name);
1060 if (result)
1061 result = dec_adb_irefcnt(adb);
1062 } else {
1063 cancel_fetches_at_name(name);
1064 if (!NAME_DEAD(name)) {
1065 bucket = name->lock_bucket;
1066 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->names[bucket], name, plink);
1067 ISC_LIST_APPEND(adb->deadnames[bucket], name, plink);
1068 name->flags |= NAME_IS_DEAD;
1069 }
1070 }
1071 return (result);
1072}
1073
1074/*
1075 * Requires the name's bucket be locked and no entry buckets be locked.
1076 */
1077static bool
1078check_expire_namehooks(dns_adbname_t *name, isc_stdtime_t now) {
1079 dns_adb_t *adb;
1080 bool result4 = false;
1081 bool result6 = false;
1082
1083 INSIST(DNS_ADBNAME_VALID(name));
1084 adb = name->adb;
1085 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
1086
1087 /*
1088 * Check to see if we need to remove the v4 addresses
1089 */
1090 if (!NAME_FETCH_V4(name) && EXPIRE_OK(name->expire_v4, now)) {
1091 if (NAME_HAS_V4(name)) {
1092 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "expiring v4 for name %p", name);
1093 result4 = clean_namehooks(adb, &name->v4);
1094 name->partial_result &= ~DNS_ADBFIND_INET;
1095 }
1096 name->expire_v4 = INT_MAX;
1097 name->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_UNEXPECTED;
1098 }
1099
1100 /*
1101 * Check to see if we need to remove the v6 addresses
1102 */
1103 if (!NAME_FETCH_V6(name) && EXPIRE_OK(name->expire_v6, now)) {
1104 if (NAME_HAS_V6(name)) {
1105 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "expiring v6 for name %p", name);
1106 result6 = clean_namehooks(adb, &name->v6);
1107 name->partial_result &= ~DNS_ADBFIND_INET6;
1108 }
1109 name->expire_v6 = INT_MAX;
1110 name->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_UNEXPECTED;
1111 }
1112
1113 /*
1114 * Check to see if we need to remove the alias target.
1115 */
1116 if (EXPIRE_OK(name->expire_target, now)) {
1117 clean_target(adb, &name->target);
1118 name->expire_target = INT_MAX;
1119 }
1120 return (result4 || result6);
1121}

1123/*
1124 * Requires the name's bucket be locked.
1125 */
1126static inline void
1127link_name(dns_adb_t *adb, int bucket, dns_adbname_t *name) {
1128 INSIST(name->lock_bucket == DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
1129
1130 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(adb->names[bucket], name, plink);
1131 name->lock_bucket = bucket;
1132 adb->name_refcnt[bucket]++;
1133}
1134
1135/*
1136 * Requires the name's bucket be locked.
1137 */
1138static inline bool
1139unlink_name(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbname_t *name) {
1140 int bucket;
1141 bool result = false;
1142
1143 bucket = name->lock_bucket;
1144 INSIST(bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
1145
1146 if (NAME_DEAD(name))
1147 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->deadnames[bucket], name, plink);
1148 else
1149 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->names[bucket], name, plink);
1150 name->lock_bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
1151 INSIST(adb->name_refcnt[bucket] > 0);
1152 adb->name_refcnt[bucket]--;
1153 if (adb->name_sd[bucket] && adb->name_refcnt[bucket] == 0)
1154 result = true;
1155 return (result);
1156}
1157
1158/*
1159 * Requires the entry's bucket be locked.
1160 */
1161static inline void
1162link_entry(dns_adb_t *adb, int bucket, dns_adbentry_t *entry) {
1163 int i;
1164 dns_adbentry_t *e;
1165
1166 if (isc_mem_isovermem(adb->mctx)) {
1167 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
1168 e = ISC_LIST_TAIL(adb->entries[bucket]);
1169 if (e == NULL)
1170 break;
1171 if (e->refcnt == 0) {
1172 unlink_entry(adb, e);
1173 free_adbentry(adb, &e);
1174 continue;
1175 }
1176 INSIST((e->flags & ENTRY_IS_DEAD) == 0);
1177 e->flags |= ENTRY_IS_DEAD;
1178 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->entries[bucket], e, plink);
1179 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(adb->deadentries[bucket], e, plink);
1180 }
1181 }
1182
1183 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(adb->entries[bucket], entry, plink);
1184 entry->lock_bucket = bucket;
1185 adb->entry_refcnt[bucket]++;
1186}
1187
1188/*
1189 * Requires the entry's bucket be locked.
1190 */
1191static inline bool
1192unlink_entry(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbentry_t *entry) {
1193 int bucket;
1194 bool result = false;
1195
1196 bucket = entry->lock_bucket;
1197 INSIST(bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
1198
1199 if ((entry->flags & ENTRY_IS_DEAD) != 0)
1200 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->deadentries[bucket], entry, plink);
1201 else
1202 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->entries[bucket], entry, plink);
1203 entry->lock_bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
1204 INSIST(adb->entry_refcnt[bucket] > 0);
1205 adb->entry_refcnt[bucket]--;
1206 if (adb->entry_sd[bucket] && adb->entry_refcnt[bucket] == 0)
1207 result = true;
1208 return (result);
1209}
1210
1211static inline void
1212violate_locking_hierarchy(isc_mutex_t *have, isc_mutex_t *want) {
1213 if (isc_mutex_trylock(want) != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1214 UNLOCK(have);
1215 LOCK(want);
1216 LOCK(have);
1217 }
1218}
1219
1220/*
1221 * The ADB _MUST_ be locked before calling. Also, exit conditions must be
1222 * checked after calling this function.
1223 */
1224static bool
1225shutdown_names(dns_adb_t *adb) {
1226 unsigned int bucket;
1227 bool result = false;
1228 dns_adbname_t *name;
1229 dns_adbname_t *next_name;
1230
1231 for (bucket = 0; bucket < adb->nnames; bucket++) {
1232 LOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
1233 adb->name_sd[bucket] = true;
1234
1235 name = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->names[bucket]);
1236 if (name == NULL) {
1237 /*
1238 * This bucket has no names. We must decrement the
1239 * irefcnt ourselves, since it will not be
1240 * automatically triggered by a name being unlinked.
1241 */
1242 INSIST(result == false);
1243 result = dec_adb_irefcnt(adb);
1244 } else {
1245 /*
1246 * Run through the list. For each name, clean up finds
1247 * found there, and cancel any fetches running. When
1248 * all the fetches are canceled, the name will destroy
1249 * itself.
1250 */
1251 while (name != NULL) {
1252 next_name = ISC_LIST_NEXT(name, plink);
1253 INSIST(result == false);
1254 result = kill_name(&name,
1255 DNS_EVENT_ADBSHUTDOWN);
1256 name = next_name;
1257 }
1258 }
1259
1260 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
1261 }
1262 return (result);
1263}
1264
1265/*
1266 * The ADB _MUST_ be locked before calling. Also, exit conditions must be
1267 * checked after calling this function.
1268 */
1269static bool
1270shutdown_entries(dns_adb_t *adb) {
1271 unsigned int bucket;
1272 bool result = false;
1273 dns_adbentry_t *entry;
1274 dns_adbentry_t *next_entry;
1275
1276 for (bucket = 0; bucket < adb->nentries; bucket++) {
1277 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
1278 adb->entry_sd[bucket] = true;
1279
1280 entry = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->entries[bucket]);
1281 if (adb->entry_refcnt[bucket] == 0) {
1282 /*
1283 * This bucket has no entries. We must decrement the
1284 * irefcnt ourselves, since it will not be
1285 * automatically triggered by an entry being unlinked.
1286 */
1287 result = dec_adb_irefcnt(adb);
1288 } else {
1289 /*
1290 * Run through the list. Cleanup any entries not
1291 * associated with names, and which are not in use.
1292 */
1293 while (entry != NULL) {
1294 next_entry = ISC_LIST_NEXT(entry, plink);
1295 if (entry->refcnt == 0 &&
1296 entry->expires != 0) {
1297 result = unlink_entry(adb, entry);
1298 free_adbentry(adb, &entry);
1299 if (result)
1300 result = dec_adb_irefcnt(adb);
1301 }
1302 entry = next_entry;
1303 }
1304 }
1305
1306 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
1307 }
1308 return (result);
1309}

1311/*
1312 * Name bucket must be locked
1313 */
1314static void
1315cancel_fetches_at_name(dns_adbname_t *name) {
1316 if (NAME_FETCH_A(name))
1317 dns_resolver_cancelfetch(name->fetch_a->fetch);
1318
1319 if (NAME_FETCH_AAAA(name))
1320 dns_resolver_cancelfetch(name->fetch_aaaa->fetch);
1321}

1323/*
1324 * Assumes the name bucket is locked.
1325 */
1326static bool
1327clean_namehooks(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbnamehooklist_t *namehooks) {
1328 dns_adbentry_t *entry;
1329 dns_adbnamehook_t *namehook;
1330 int addr_bucket;
1331 bool result = false;
1332 bool overmem = isc_mem_isovermem(adb->mctx);
1333
1334 addr_bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
1335 namehook = ISC_LIST_HEAD(*namehooks);
1336 while (namehook != NULL) {
1337 INSIST(DNS_ADBNAMEHOOK_VALID(namehook));
1338
1339 /*
1340 * Clean up the entry if needed.
1341 */
1342 entry = namehook->entry;
1343 if (entry != NULL) {
1344 INSIST(DNS_ADBENTRY_VALID(entry));
1345
1346 if (addr_bucket != entry->lock_bucket) {
1347 if (addr_bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET)
1348 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[addr_bucket]);
1349 addr_bucket = entry->lock_bucket;
1350 INSIST(addr_bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
1351 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[addr_bucket]);
1352 }
1353
1354 entry->nh--;
1355 result = dec_entry_refcnt(adb, overmem, entry,
1356 false);
1357 }
1358
1359 /*
1360 * Free the namehook
1361 */
1362 namehook->entry = NULL;
1363 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(*namehooks, namehook, plink);
1364 free_adbnamehook(adb, &namehook);
1365
1366 namehook = ISC_LIST_HEAD(*namehooks);
1367 }
1368
1369 if (addr_bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET)
1370 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[addr_bucket]);
1371 return (result);
1372}

1374static void
1375clean_target(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_name_t *target) {
1376 if (dns_name_countlabels(target) > 0) {
1377 dns_name_free(target, adb->mctx);
1378 dns_name_init(target, NULL);
1379 }
1380}
1381
1382static isc_result_t
1383set_target(dns_adb_t *adb, const dns_name_t *name, const dns_name_t *fname,
1384 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_name_t *target)
1385{
1386 isc_result_t result;
1387 dns_namereln_t namereln;
1388 unsigned int nlabels;
1389 int order;
1390 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
1391 dns_fixedname_t fixed1, fixed2;
1392 dns_name_t *prefix, *new_target;
1393
1394 REQUIRE(dns_name_countlabels(target) == 0);
1395
1396 if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_cname) {
1397 dns_rdata_cname_t cname;
1398
1399 /*
1400 * Copy the CNAME's target into the target name.
1401 */
1402 result = dns_rdataset_first(rdataset);
1403 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1404 return (result);
1405 dns_rdataset_current(rdataset, &rdata);
1406 result = dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata, &cname, NULL);
1407 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1408 return (result);
1409 result = dns_name_dup(&cname.cname, adb->mctx, target);
1410 dns_rdata_freestruct(&cname);
1411 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1412 return (result);
1413 } else {
1414 dns_rdata_dname_t dname;
1415
1416 INSIST(rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_dname);
1417 namereln = dns_name_fullcompare(name, fname, &order, &nlabels);
1418 INSIST(namereln == dns_namereln_subdomain);
1419 /*
1420 * Get the target name of the DNAME.
1421 */
1422 result = dns_rdataset_first(rdataset);
1423 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1424 return (result);
1425 dns_rdataset_current(rdataset, &rdata);
1426 result = dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata, &dname, NULL);
1427 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1428 return (result);
1429 /*
1430 * Construct the new target name.
1431 */
1432 prefix = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed1);
1433 new_target = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed2);
1434 dns_name_split(name, nlabels, prefix, NULL);
1435 result = dns_name_concatenate(prefix, &dname.dname, new_target,
1436 NULL);
1437 dns_rdata_freestruct(&dname);
1438 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1439 return (result);
1440 result = dns_name_dup(new_target, adb->mctx, target);
1441 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1442 return (result);
1443 }
1444
1445 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1446}
1447
1448/*
1449 * Assumes nothing is locked, since this is called by the client.
1450 */
1451static void
1452event_free(isc_event_t *event) {
1453 dns_adbfind_t *find;
1454
1455 INSIST(event != NULL);
1456 find = event->ev_destroy_arg;
1457 INSIST(DNS_ADBFIND_VALID(find));
1458
1459 LOCK(&find->lock);
1460 find->flags |= FIND_EVENT_FREED;
1461 event->ev_destroy_arg = NULL;
1462 UNLOCK(&find->lock);
1463}
1464
1465/*
1466 * Assumes the name bucket is locked.
1467 */
1468static void
1469clean_finds_at_name(dns_adbname_t *name, isc_eventtype_t evtype,
1470 unsigned int addrs)
1471{
1472 isc_event_t *ev;
1473 isc_task_t *task;
1474 dns_adbfind_t *find;
1475 dns_adbfind_t *next_find;
1476 bool process;
1477 unsigned int wanted, notify;
1478
1479 DP(ENTER_LEVEL,
1480 "ENTER clean_finds_at_name, name %p, evtype %08x, addrs %08x",
1481 name, evtype, addrs);
1482
1483 find = ISC_LIST_HEAD(name->finds);
1484 while (find != NULL) {
1485 LOCK(&find->lock);
1486 next_find = ISC_LIST_NEXT(find, plink);
1487
1488 process = false;
1489 wanted = find->flags & DNS_ADBFIND_ADDRESSMASK;
1490 notify = wanted & addrs;
1491
1492 switch (evtype) {
1493 case DNS_EVENT_ADBMOREADDRESSES:
1494 DP(ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3), "DNS_EVENT_ADBMOREADDRESSES");
1495 if ((notify) != 0) {
1496 find->flags &= ~addrs;
1497 process = true;
1498 }
1499 break;
1500 case DNS_EVENT_ADBNOMOREADDRESSES:
1501 DP(ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3), "DNS_EVENT_ADBNOMOREADDRESSES");
1502 find->flags &= ~addrs;
1503 wanted = find->flags & DNS_ADBFIND_ADDRESSMASK;
1504 if (wanted == 0)
1505 process = true;
1506 break;
1507 default:
1508 find->flags &= ~addrs;
1509 process = true;
1510 }
1511
1512 if (process) {
1513 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "cfan: processing find %p", find);
1514 /*
1515 * Unlink the find from the name, letting the caller
1516 * call dns_adb_destroyfind() on it to clean it up
1517 * later.
1518 */
1519 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(name->finds, find, plink);
1520 find->adbname = NULL;
1521 find->name_bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
1522
1523 INSIST(!FIND_EVENTSENT(find));
1524
1525 ev = &find->event;
1526 task = ev->ev_sender;
1527 ev->ev_sender = find;
1528 find->result_v4 = find_err_map[name->fetch_err];
1529 find->result_v6 = find_err_map[name->fetch6_err];
1530 ev->ev_type = evtype;
1531 ev->ev_destroy = event_free;
1532 ev->ev_destroy_arg = find;
1533
1534 DP(DEF_LEVEL,
1535 "sending event %p to task %p for find %p",
1536 ev, task, find);
1537
1538 isc_task_sendanddetach(&task, (isc_event_t **)&ev);
1539 find->flags |= FIND_EVENT_SENT;
1540 } else {
1541 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "cfan: skipping find %p", find);
1542 }
1543
1544 UNLOCK(&find->lock);
1545 find = next_find;
1546 }
1547 DP(ENTER_LEVEL, "EXIT clean_finds_at_name, name %p", name);
1548}
1549
1550static inline void
1551check_exit(dns_adb_t *adb) {
1552 isc_event_t *event;
1553 /*
1554 * The caller must be holding the adb lock.
1555 */
1556 if (adb->shutting_down) {
1557 /*
1558 * If there aren't any external references either, we're
1559 * done. Send the control event to initiate shutdown.
1560 */
1561 INSIST(!adb->cevent_out); /* Sanity check. */
1562 ISC_EVENT_INIT(&adb->cevent, sizeof(adb->cevent), 0, NULL,
1563 DNS_EVENT_ADBCONTROL, shutdown_task, adb,
1564 adb, NULL, NULL);
1565 event = &adb->cevent;
1566 isc_task_send(adb->task, &event);
1567 adb->cevent_out = true;
1568 }
1569}
1570
1571static inline bool
1572dec_adb_irefcnt(dns_adb_t *adb) {
1573 isc_event_t *event;
1574 isc_task_t *etask;
1575 bool result = false;
1576
1577 LOCK(&adb->reflock);
1578
1579 INSIST(adb->irefcnt > 0);
1580 adb->irefcnt--;
1581
1582 if (adb->irefcnt == 0) {
1583 event = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->whenshutdown);
1584 while (event != NULL) {
1585 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->whenshutdown, event, ev_link);
1586 etask = event->ev_sender;
1587 event->ev_sender = adb;
1588 isc_task_sendanddetach(&etask, &event);
1589 event = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->whenshutdown);
1590 }
1591 }
1592
1593 if (adb->irefcnt == 0 && adb->erefcnt == 0)
1594 result = true;
1595 UNLOCK(&adb->reflock);
1596 return (result);
1597}
1598
1599static inline void
1600inc_adb_irefcnt(dns_adb_t *adb) {
1601 LOCK(&adb->reflock);
1602 adb->irefcnt++;
1603 UNLOCK(&adb->reflock);
1604}
1605
1606static inline void
1607inc_adb_erefcnt(dns_adb_t *adb) {
1608 LOCK(&adb->reflock);
1609 adb->erefcnt++;
1610 UNLOCK(&adb->reflock);
1611}
1612
1613static inline void
1614inc_entry_refcnt(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbentry_t *entry, bool lock) {
1615 int bucket;
1616
1617 bucket = entry->lock_bucket;
1618
1619 if (lock)
1620 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
1621
1622 entry->refcnt++;
1623
1624 if (lock)
1625 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
1626}
1627
1628static inline bool
1629dec_entry_refcnt(dns_adb_t *adb, bool overmem, dns_adbentry_t *entry,
1630 bool lock)
1631{
1632 int bucket;
1633 bool destroy_entry;
1634 bool result = false;
1635
1636 bucket = entry->lock_bucket;
1637
1638 if (lock)
1639 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
1640
1641 INSIST(entry->refcnt > 0);
1642 entry->refcnt--;
1643
1644 destroy_entry = false;
1645 if (entry->refcnt == 0 &&
1646 (adb->entry_sd[bucket] || entry->expires == 0 || overmem ||
1647 (entry->flags & ENTRY_IS_DEAD) != 0)) {
1648 destroy_entry = true;
1649 result = unlink_entry(adb, entry);
1650 }
1651
1652 if (lock)
1653 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
1654
1655 if (!destroy_entry)
1656 return (result);
1657
1658 entry->lock_bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
1659
1660 free_adbentry(adb, &entry);
1661 if (result)
1662 result = dec_adb_irefcnt(adb);
1663
1664 return (result);
1665}

1667static inline dns_adbname_t *
1668new_adbname(dns_adb_t *adb, const dns_name_t *dnsname) {
1669 dns_adbname_t *name;
1670
1671 name = isc_mempool_get(adb->nmp);
1672 if (name == NULL)
1673 return (NULL);
1674
1675 dns_name_init(&name->name, NULL);
1676 if (dns_name_dup(dnsname, adb->mctx, &name->name) != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1677 isc_mempool_put(adb->nmp, name);
1678 return (NULL);
1679 }
1680 dns_name_init(&name->target, NULL);
1681 name->magic = DNS_ADBNAME_MAGIC;
1682 name->adb = adb;
1683 name->partial_result = 0;
1684 name->flags = 0;
1685 name->expire_v4 = INT_MAX;
1686 name->expire_v6 = INT_MAX;
1687 name->expire_target = INT_MAX;
1688 name->chains = 0;
1689 name->lock_bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
1690 ISC_LIST_INIT(name->v4);
1691 ISC_LIST_INIT(name->v6);
1692 name->fetch_a = NULL;
1693 name->fetch_aaaa = NULL;
1694 name->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_UNEXPECTED;
1695 name->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_UNEXPECTED;
1696 ISC_LIST_INIT(name->finds);
1697 ISC_LINK_INIT(name, plink);
1698
1699 LOCK(&adb->namescntlock);
1700 adb->namescnt++;
1701 inc_adbstats(adb, dns_adbstats_namescnt);
1702 if (!adb->grownames_sent && adb->excl != NULL &&
1703 adb->namescnt > (adb->nnames * 8))
1704 {
1705 isc_event_t *event = &adb->grownames;
1706 inc_adb_irefcnt(adb);
1707 isc_task_send(adb->excl, &event);
1708 adb->grownames_sent = true;
1709 }
1710 UNLOCK(&adb->namescntlock);
1711
1712 return (name);
1713}

1715static inline void
1716free_adbname(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbname_t **name) {
1717 dns_adbname_t *n;
1718
1719 INSIST(name != NULL && DNS_ADBNAME_VALID(*name));
1720 n = *name;
1721 *name = NULL;
1722
1723 INSIST(!NAME_HAS_V4(n));
1724 INSIST(!NAME_HAS_V6(n));
1725 INSIST(!NAME_FETCH(n));
1726 INSIST(ISC_LIST_EMPTY(n->finds));
1727 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(n, plink));
1728 INSIST(n->lock_bucket == DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
1729 INSIST(n->adb == adb);
1730
1731 n->magic = 0;
1732 dns_name_free(&n->name, adb->mctx);
1733
1734 isc_mempool_put(adb->nmp, n);
1735 LOCK(&adb->namescntlock);
1736 adb->namescnt--;
1737 dec_adbstats(adb, dns_adbstats_namescnt);
1738 UNLOCK(&adb->namescntlock);
1739}

1861static inline void
1862free_adbentry(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbentry_t **entry) {
1863 dns_adbentry_t *e;
1864 dns_adblameinfo_t *li;
1865
1866 INSIST(entry != NULL && DNS_ADBENTRY_VALID(*entry));
1867 e = *entry;
1868 *entry = NULL;
1869
1870 INSIST(e->lock_bucket == DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
1871 INSIST(e->refcnt == 0);
1872 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(e, plink));
1873
1874 e->magic = 0;
1875
1876 if (e->cookie != NULL)
1877 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, e->cookie, e->cookielen);
1878
1879 li = ISC_LIST_HEAD(e->lameinfo);
1880 while (li != NULL) {
1881 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(e->lameinfo, li, plink);
1882 free_adblameinfo(adb, &li);
1883 li = ISC_LIST_HEAD(e->lameinfo);
1884 }
1885
1886 isc_mempool_put(adb->emp, e);
1887 LOCK(&adb->entriescntlock);
1888 adb->entriescnt--;
1889 dec_adbstats(adb, dns_adbstats_entriescnt);
1890 UNLOCK(&adb->entriescntlock);
1891}

2026/*
2027 * Search for the name. NOTE: The bucket is kept locked on both
2028 * success and failure, so it must always be unlocked by the caller!
2029 *
2030 * On the first call to this function, *bucketp must be set to
2031 * DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET.
2032 */
2033static inline dns_adbname_t *
2034find_name_and_lock(dns_adb_t *adb, const dns_name_t *name,
2035 unsigned int options, int *bucketp)
2036{
2037 dns_adbname_t *adbname;
2038 int bucket;
2039
2040 bucket = dns_name_fullhash(name, false) % adb->nnames;
2041
2042 if (*bucketp == DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET) {
2043 LOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
2044 *bucketp = bucket;
2045 } else if (*bucketp != bucket) {
2046 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[*bucketp]);
2047 LOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
2048 *bucketp = bucket;
2049 }
2050
2051 adbname = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->names[bucket]);
2052 while (adbname != NULL) {
2053 if (!NAME_DEAD(adbname)) {
2054 if (dns_name_equal(name, &adbname->name)
2055 && GLUEHINT_OK(adbname, options)
2056 && STARTATZONE_MATCHES(adbname, options))
2057 return (adbname);
2058 }
2059 adbname = ISC_LIST_NEXT(adbname, plink);
2060 }
2061
2062 return (NULL);
2063}
2064
2065/*
2066 * Search for the address. NOTE: The bucket is kept locked on both
2067 * success and failure, so it must always be unlocked by the caller.
2068 *
2069 * On the first call to this function, *bucketp must be set to
2070 * DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET. This will cause a lock to occur. On
2071 * later calls (within the same "lock path") it can be left alone, so
2072 * if this function is called multiple times locking is only done if
2073 * the bucket changes.
2074 */
2075static inline dns_adbentry_t *
2076find_entry_and_lock(dns_adb_t *adb, const isc_sockaddr_t *addr, int *bucketp,
2077 isc_stdtime_t now)
2078{
2079 dns_adbentry_t *entry, *entry_next;
2080 int bucket;
2081
2082 bucket = isc_sockaddr_hash(addr, true) % adb->nentries;
2083
2084 if (*bucketp == DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET) {
2085 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
2086 *bucketp = bucket;
2087 } else if (*bucketp != bucket) {
2088 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[*bucketp]);
2089 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
2090 *bucketp = bucket;
2091 }
2092
2093 /* Search the list, while cleaning up expired entries. */
2094 for (entry = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->entries[bucket]);
2095 entry != NULL;
2096 entry = entry_next) {
2097 entry_next = ISC_LIST_NEXT(entry, plink);
2098 (void)check_expire_entry(adb, &entry, now);
2099 if (entry != NULL &&
2100 (entry->expires == 0 || entry->expires > now) &&
2101 isc_sockaddr_equal(addr, &entry->sockaddr)) {
2102 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->entries[bucket], entry, plink);
2103 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(adb->entries[bucket], entry, plink);
2104 return (entry);
2105 }
2106 }
2107
2108 return (NULL);
2109}
2110
2111/*
2112 * Entry bucket MUST be locked!
2113 */
2114static bool
2115entry_is_lame(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbentry_t *entry, const dns_name_t *qname,
2116 dns_rdatatype_t qtype, isc_stdtime_t now)
2117{
2118 dns_adblameinfo_t *li, *next_li;
2119 bool is_bad;
2120
2121 is_bad = false;
2122
2123 li = ISC_LIST_HEAD(entry->lameinfo);
2124 if (li == NULL)
2125 return (false);
2126 while (li != NULL) {
2127 next_li = ISC_LIST_NEXT(li, plink);
2128
2129 /*
2130 * Has the entry expired?
2131 */
2132 if (li->lame_timer < now) {
2133 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(entry->lameinfo, li, plink);
2134 free_adblameinfo(adb, &li);
2135 }
2136
2137 /*
2138 * Order tests from least to most expensive.
2139 *
2140 * We do not break out of the main loop here as
2141 * we use the loop for house keeping.
2142 */
2143 if (li != NULL && !is_bad && li->qtype == qtype &&
2144 dns_name_equal(qname, &li->qname))
2145 is_bad = true;
2146
2147 li = next_li;
2148 }
2149
2150 return (is_bad);
2151}

2153static void
2154log_quota(dns_adbentry_t *entry, const char *fmt, ...) {
2155 va_list ap;
2156 char msgbuf[2048];
2157 char addrbuf[ISC_NETADDR_FORMATSIZE];
2158 isc_netaddr_t netaddr;
2159
2160 va_start(ap, fmt);
2161 vsnprintf(msgbuf, sizeof(msgbuf), fmt, ap);
2162 va_end(ap);
2163
2164 isc_netaddr_fromsockaddr(&netaddr, &entry->sockaddr);
2165 isc_netaddr_format(&netaddr, addrbuf, sizeof(addrbuf));
2166
2167 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE, DNS_LOGMODULE_ADB,
2168 ISC_LOG_INFO, "adb: quota %s (%u/%u): %s",
2169 addrbuf, entry->active, entry->quota, msgbuf);
2170}

2172static void
2173copy_namehook_lists(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbfind_t *find,
2174 const dns_name_t *qname, dns_rdatatype_t qtype,
2175 dns_adbname_t *name, isc_stdtime_t now)
2176{
2177 dns_adbnamehook_t *namehook;
2178 dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addrinfo;
2179 dns_adbentry_t *entry;
2180 int bucket;
2181
2182 bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
2183
2184 if ((find->options & DNS_ADBFIND_INET) != 0) {
2185 namehook = ISC_LIST_HEAD(name->v4);
2186 while (namehook != NULL) {
2187 entry = namehook->entry;
2188 bucket = entry->lock_bucket;
2189 INSIST(bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
2190 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
2191
2192 if (entry->quota != 0 &&
2193 entry->active >= entry->quota)
2194 {
2195 find->options |=
2196 (DNS_ADBFIND_LAMEPRUNED|
2197 DNS_ADBFIND_OVERQUOTA);
2198 goto nextv4;
2199 }
2200
2201 if (!FIND_RETURNLAME(find)
2202 && entry_is_lame(adb, entry, qname, qtype, now)) {
2203 find->options |= DNS_ADBFIND_LAMEPRUNED;
2204 goto nextv4;
2205 }
2206 addrinfo = new_adbaddrinfo(adb, entry, find->port);
2207 if (addrinfo == NULL) {
2208 find->partial_result |= DNS_ADBFIND_INET;
2209 goto out;
2210 }
2211 /*
2212 * Found a valid entry. Add it to the find's list.
2213 */
2214 inc_entry_refcnt(adb, entry, false);
2215 ISC_LIST_APPEND(find->list, addrinfo, publink);
2216 addrinfo = NULL;
2217 nextv4:
2218 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
2219 bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
2220 namehook = ISC_LIST_NEXT(namehook, plink);
2221 }
2222 }
2223
2224 if ((find->options & DNS_ADBFIND_INET6) != 0) {
2225 namehook = ISC_LIST_HEAD(name->v6);
2226 while (namehook != NULL) {
2227 entry = namehook->entry;
2228 bucket = entry->lock_bucket;
2229 INSIST(bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
2230 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
2231
2232 if (entry->quota != 0 &&
2233 entry->active >= entry->quota)
2234 {
2235 find->options |=
2236 (DNS_ADBFIND_LAMEPRUNED|
2237 DNS_ADBFIND_OVERQUOTA);
2238 goto nextv6;
2239 }
2240
2241 if (!FIND_RETURNLAME(find)
2242 && entry_is_lame(adb, entry, qname, qtype, now)) {
2243 find->options |= DNS_ADBFIND_LAMEPRUNED;
2244 goto nextv6;
2245 }
2246 addrinfo = new_adbaddrinfo(adb, entry, find->port);
2247 if (addrinfo == NULL) {
2248 find->partial_result |= DNS_ADBFIND_INET6;
2249 goto out;
2250 }
2251 /*
2252 * Found a valid entry. Add it to the find's list.
2253 */
2254 inc_entry_refcnt(adb, entry, false);
2255 ISC_LIST_APPEND(find->list, addrinfo, publink);
2256 addrinfo = NULL;
2257 nextv6:
2258 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
2259 bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
2260 namehook = ISC_LIST_NEXT(namehook, plink);
2261 }
2262 }
2263
2264 out:
2265 if (bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET)
2266 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
2267}

2269static void
2270shutdown_task(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *ev) {
2271 dns_adb_t *adb;
2272
2273 UNUSED(task);
2274
2275 adb = ev->ev_arg;
2276 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
2277
2278 isc_event_free(&ev);
2279 /*
2280 * Wait for lock around check_exit() call to be released.
2281 */
2282 LOCK(&adb->lock);
2283 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
2284 destroy(adb);
2285}

2287/*
2288 * Name bucket must be locked; adb may be locked; no other locks held.
2289 */
2290static bool
2291check_expire_name(dns_adbname_t **namep, isc_stdtime_t now) {
2292 dns_adbname_t *name;
2293 bool result = false;
2294
2295 INSIST(namep != NULL && DNS_ADBNAME_VALID(*namep));
2296 name = *namep;
2297
2298 if (NAME_HAS_V4(name) || NAME_HAS_V6(name))
2299 return (result);
2300 if (NAME_FETCH(name))
2301 return (result);
2302 if (!EXPIRE_OK(name->expire_v4, now))
2303 return (result);
2304 if (!EXPIRE_OK(name->expire_v6, now))
2305 return (result);
2306 if (!EXPIRE_OK(name->expire_target, now))
2307 return (result);
2308
2309 /*
2310 * The name is empty. Delete it.
2311 */
2312 result = kill_name(&name, DNS_EVENT_ADBEXPIRED);
2313 *namep = NULL;
2314
2315 /*
2316 * Our caller, or one of its callers, will be calling check_exit() at
2317 * some point, so we don't need to do it here.
2318 */
2319 return (result);
2320}
2321
2322/*%
2323 * Examine the tail entry of the LRU list to see if it expires or is stale
2324 * (unused for some period); if so, the name entry will be freed. If the ADB
2325 * is in the overmem condition, the tail and the next to tail entries
2326 * will be unconditionally removed (unless they have an outstanding fetch).
2327 * We don't care about a race on 'overmem' at the risk of causing some
2328 * collateral damage or a small delay in starting cleanup, so we don't bother
2329 * to lock ADB (if it's not locked).
2330 *
2331 * Name bucket must be locked; adb may be locked; no other locks held.
2332 */
2333static void
2334check_stale_name(dns_adb_t *adb, int bucket, isc_stdtime_t now) {
2335 int victims, max_victims;
2336 dns_adbname_t *victim, *next_victim;
2337 bool overmem = isc_mem_isovermem(adb->mctx);
2338 int scans = 0;
2339
2340 INSIST(bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
2341
2342 max_victims = overmem ? 2 : 1;
2343
2344 /*
2345 * We limit the number of scanned entries to 10 (arbitrary choice)
2346 * in order to avoid examining too many entries when there are many
2347 * tail entries that have fetches (this should be rare, but could
2348 * happen).
2349 */
2350 victim = ISC_LIST_TAIL(adb->names[bucket]);
2351 for (victims = 0;
2352 victim != NULL && victims < max_victims && scans < 10;
2353 victim = next_victim) {
2354 INSIST(!NAME_DEAD(victim));
2355 scans++;
2356 next_victim = ISC_LIST_PREV(victim, plink);
2357 (void)check_expire_name(&victim, now);
2358 if (victim == NULL) {
2359 victims++;
2360 goto next;
2361 }
2362
2363 if (!NAME_FETCH(victim) &&
2364 (overmem || victim->last_used + ADB_STALE_MARGIN <= now)) {
2365 RUNTIME_CHECK(kill_name(&victim,
2366 DNS_EVENT_ADBCANCELED) ==
2367 false);
2368 victims++;
2369 }
2370
2371 next:
2372 if (!overmem)
2373 break;
2374 }
2375}

2377/*
2378 * Entry bucket must be locked; adb may be locked; no other locks held.
2379 */
2380static bool
2381check_expire_entry(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbentry_t **entryp, isc_stdtime_t now)
2382{
2383 dns_adbentry_t *entry;
2384 bool result = false;
2385
2386 INSIST(entryp != NULL && DNS_ADBENTRY_VALID(*entryp));
2387 entry = *entryp;
2388
2389 if (entry->refcnt != 0)
2390 return (result);
2391
2392 if (entry->expires == 0 || entry->expires > now)
2393 return (result);
2394
2395 /*
2396 * The entry is not in use. Delete it.
2397 */
2398 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "killing entry %p", entry);
2399 INSIST(ISC_LINK_LINKED(entry, plink));
2400 result = unlink_entry(adb, entry);
2401 free_adbentry(adb, &entry);
2402 if (result)
2403 dec_adb_irefcnt(adb);
2404 *entryp = NULL;
2405 return (result);
2406}

2408/*
2409 * ADB must be locked, and no other locks held.
2410 */
2411static bool
2412cleanup_names(dns_adb_t *adb, int bucket, isc_stdtime_t now) {
2413 dns_adbname_t *name;
2414 dns_adbname_t *next_name;
2415 bool result = false;
2416
2417 DP(CLEAN_LEVEL, "cleaning name bucket %d", bucket);
2418
2419 LOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
2420 if (adb->name_sd[bucket]) {
2421 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
2422 return (result);
2423 }
2424
2425 name = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->names[bucket]);
2426 while (name != NULL) {
2427 next_name = ISC_LIST_NEXT(name, plink);
2428 INSIST(result == false);
2429 result = check_expire_namehooks(name, now);
2430 if (!result)
2431 result = check_expire_name(&name, now);
2432 name = next_name;
2433 }
2434 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
2435 return (result);
2436}

2438/*
2439 * ADB must be locked, and no other locks held.
2440 */
2441static bool
2442cleanup_entries(dns_adb_t *adb, int bucket, isc_stdtime_t now) {
2443 dns_adbentry_t *entry, *next_entry;
2444 bool result = false;
2445
2446 DP(CLEAN_LEVEL, "cleaning entry bucket %d", bucket);
2447
2448 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
2449 entry = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->entries[bucket]);
2450 while (entry != NULL) {
2451 next_entry = ISC_LIST_NEXT(entry, plink);
2452 INSIST(result == false);
2453 result = check_expire_entry(adb, &entry, now);
2454 entry = next_entry;
2455 }
2456 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
2457 return (result);
2458}

2460static void
2461destroy(dns_adb_t *adb) {
2462 adb->magic = 0;
2463
2464 isc_task_detach(&adb->task);
2465 if (adb->excl != NULL)
2466 isc_task_detach(&adb->excl);
2467
2468 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->nmp);
2469 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->nhmp);
2470 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->limp);
2471 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->emp);
2472 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->ahmp);
2473 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->aimp);
2474 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->afmp);
2475
2476 isc_mutexblock_destroy(adb->entrylocks, adb->nentries);
2477 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entries,
2478 sizeof(*adb->entries) * adb->nentries);
2479 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->deadentries,
2480 sizeof(*adb->deadentries) * adb->nentries);
2481 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entrylocks,
2482 sizeof(*adb->entrylocks) * adb->nentries);
2483 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entry_sd,
2484 sizeof(*adb->entry_sd) * adb->nentries);
2485 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entry_refcnt,
2486 sizeof(*adb->entry_refcnt) * adb->nentries);
2487
2488 isc_mutexblock_destroy(adb->namelocks, adb->nnames);
2489 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->names,
2490 sizeof(*adb->names) * adb->nnames);
2491 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->deadnames,
2492 sizeof(*adb->deadnames) * adb->nnames);
2493 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->namelocks,
2494 sizeof(*adb->namelocks) * adb->nnames);
2495 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->name_sd,
2496 sizeof(*adb->name_sd) * adb->nnames);
2497 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->name_refcnt,
2498 sizeof(*adb->name_refcnt) * adb->nnames);
2499
2500 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->reflock);
2501 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->lock);
2502 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->mplock);
2503 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->overmemlock);
2504 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->entriescntlock);
2505 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->namescntlock);
2506
2507 isc_mem_putanddetach(&adb->mctx, adb, sizeof(dns_adb_t));
2508}
