2515isc_result_t
2516dns_adb_create(isc_mem_t *mem, dns_view_t *view, isc_timermgr_t *timermgr,
2517 isc_taskmgr_t *taskmgr, dns_adb_t **newadb)
2518{
2519 dns_adb_t *adb;
2520 isc_result_t result;
2521 unsigned int i;
2522
2523 REQUIRE(mem != NULL);
2524 REQUIRE(view != NULL);
2525 REQUIRE(timermgr != NULL); /* this is actually unused */
2526 REQUIRE(taskmgr != NULL);
2527 REQUIRE(newadb != NULL && *newadb == NULL);
2528
2529 UNUSED(timermgr);
2530
2531 adb = isc_mem_get(mem, sizeof(dns_adb_t));
2532 if (adb == NULL)
2533 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
2534
2535 /*
2536 * Initialize things here that cannot fail, and especially things
2537 * that must be NULL for the error return to work properly.
2538 */
2539 adb->magic = 0;
2540 adb->erefcnt = 1;
2541 adb->irefcnt = 0;
2542 adb->nmp = NULL;
2543 adb->nhmp = NULL;
2544 adb->limp = NULL;
2545 adb->emp = NULL;
2546 adb->ahmp = NULL;
2547 adb->aimp = NULL;
2548 adb->afmp = NULL;
2549 adb->task = NULL;
2550 adb->excl = NULL;
2551 adb->mctx = NULL;
2552 adb->view = view;
2553 adb->taskmgr = taskmgr;
2554 adb->next_cleanbucket = 0;
2555 ISC_EVENT_INIT(&adb->cevent, sizeof(adb->cevent),
2556 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
2557 adb->cevent_out = false;
2558 adb->shutting_down = false;
2559 ISC_LIST_INIT(adb->whenshutdown);
2560
2561 adb->nentries = nbuckets[0];
2562 adb->entriescnt = 0;
2563 adb->entries = NULL;
2564 adb->deadentries = NULL;
2565 adb->entry_sd = NULL;
2566 adb->entry_refcnt = NULL;
2567 adb->entrylocks = NULL;
2568 ISC_EVENT_INIT(&adb->growentries, sizeof(adb->growentries), 0, NULL,
2569 DNS_EVENT_ADBGROWENTRIES, grow_entries, adb,
2570 adb, NULL, NULL);
2571 adb->growentries_sent = false;
2572
2573 adb->quota = 0;
2574 adb->atr_freq = 0;
2575 adb->atr_low = 0.0;
2576 adb->atr_high = 0.0;
2577 adb->atr_discount = 0.0;
2578
2579 adb->nnames = nbuckets[0];
2580 adb->namescnt = 0;
2581 adb->names = NULL;
2582 adb->deadnames = NULL;
2583 adb->name_sd = NULL;
2584 adb->name_refcnt = NULL;
2585 adb->namelocks = NULL;
2586 ISC_EVENT_INIT(&adb->grownames, sizeof(adb->grownames), 0, NULL,
2587 DNS_EVENT_ADBGROWNAMES, grow_names, adb,
2588 adb, NULL, NULL);
2589 adb->grownames_sent = false;
2590
2591 result = isc_taskmgr_excltask(adb->taskmgr, &adb->excl);
2592 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2593 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "adb: task-exclusive mode unavailable, "
2594 "initializing table sizes to %u\n",
2595 nbuckets[11]);
2596 adb->nentries = nbuckets[11];
2597 adb->nnames = nbuckets[11];
2598 }
2599
2600 isc_mem_attach(mem, &adb->mctx);
2601
2602 isc_mutex_init(&adb->lock);
2603 isc_mutex_init(&adb->mplock);
2604 isc_mutex_init(&adb->reflock);
2605 isc_mutex_init(&adb->overmemlock);
2606 isc_mutex_init(&adb->entriescntlock);
2607 isc_mutex_init(&adb->namescntlock);
2608
2609#define ALLOCENTRY(adb, el) \
2610 do { \
2611 (adb)->el = isc_mem_get((adb)->mctx, \
2612 sizeof(*(adb)->el) * (adb)->nentries); \
2613 if ((adb)->el == NULL) { \
2614 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY; \
2615 goto fail1; \
2616 }\
2617 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
2618 ALLOCENTRY(adb, entries);
2619 ALLOCENTRY(adb, deadentries);
2620 ALLOCENTRY(adb, entrylocks);
2621 ALLOCENTRY(adb, entry_sd);
2622 ALLOCENTRY(adb, entry_refcnt);
2623#undef ALLOCENTRY
2624
2625#define ALLOCNAME(adb, el) \
2626 do { \
2627 (adb)->el = isc_mem_get((adb)->mctx, \
2628 sizeof(*(adb)->el) * (adb)->nnames); \
2629 if ((adb)->el == NULL) { \
2630 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY; \
2631 goto fail1; \
2632 }\
2633 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
2634 ALLOCNAME(adb, names);
2635 ALLOCNAME(adb, deadnames);
2636 ALLOCNAME(adb, namelocks);
2637 ALLOCNAME(adb, name_sd);
2638 ALLOCNAME(adb, name_refcnt);
2639#undef ALLOCNAME
2640
2641 /*
2642 * Initialize the bucket locks for names and elements.
2643 * May as well initialize the list heads, too.
2644 */
2645 isc_mutexblock_init(adb->namelocks, adb->nnames);
2646
2647 for (i = 0; i < adb->nnames; i++) {
2648 ISC_LIST_INIT(adb->names[i]);
2649 ISC_LIST_INIT(adb->deadnames[i]);
2650 adb->name_sd[i] = false;
2651 adb->name_refcnt[i] = 0;
2652 adb->irefcnt++;
2653 }
2654 for (i = 0; i < adb->nentries; i++) {
2655 ISC_LIST_INIT(adb->entries[i]);
2656 ISC_LIST_INIT(adb->deadentries[i]);
2657 adb->entry_sd[i] = false;
2658 adb->entry_refcnt[i] = 0;
2659 adb->irefcnt++;
2660 }
2661 isc_mutexblock_init(adb->entrylocks, adb->nentries);
2662
2663 /*
2664 * Memory pools
2665 */
2666#define MPINIT(t, p, n) do { \
2667 result = isc_mempool_create(mem, sizeof(t), &(p)); \
2668 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) \
2669 goto fail2; \
2670 isc_mempool_setfreemax((p), FREE_ITEMS); \
2671 isc_mempool_setfillcount((p), FILL_COUNT); \
2672 isc_mempool_setname((p), n); \
2673 isc_mempool_associatelock((p), &adb->mplock); \
2674 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
2675
2676 MPINIT(dns_adbname_t, adb->nmp, "adbname");
2677 MPINIT(dns_adbnamehook_t, adb->nhmp, "adbnamehook");
2678 MPINIT(dns_adblameinfo_t, adb->limp, "adblameinfo");
2679 MPINIT(dns_adbentry_t, adb->emp, "adbentry");
2680 MPINIT(dns_adbfind_t, adb->ahmp, "adbfind");
2681 MPINIT(dns_adbaddrinfo_t, adb->aimp, "adbaddrinfo");
2682 MPINIT(dns_adbfetch_t, adb->afmp, "adbfetch");
2683
2684#undef MPINIT
2685
2686 /*
2687 * Allocate an internal task.
2688 */
2689 result = isc_task_create(adb->taskmgr, 0, &adb->task);
2690 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2691 goto fail2;
2692
2693 isc_task_setname(adb->task, "ADB", adb);
2694
2695 result = isc_stats_create(adb->mctx, &view->adbstats, dns_adbstats_max);
2696 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2697 goto fail2;
2698
2699 set_adbstat(adb, adb->nentries, dns_adbstats_nentries);
2700 set_adbstat(adb, adb->nnames, dns_adbstats_nnames);
2701
2702 /*
2703 * Normal return.
2704 */
2705 adb->magic = DNS_ADB_MAGIC;
2706 *newadb = adb;
2707 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2708
2709 fail2:
2710 if (adb->task != NULL)
2711 isc_task_detach(&adb->task);
2712
2713 /* clean up entrylocks */
2714 isc_mutexblock_destroy(adb->entrylocks, adb->nentries);
2715 isc_mutexblock_destroy(adb->namelocks, adb->nnames);
2716
2717 fail1: /* clean up only allocated memory */
2718 if (adb->entries != NULL)
2719 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entries,
2720 sizeof(*adb->entries) * adb->nentries);
2721 if (adb->deadentries != NULL)
2722 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->deadentries,
2723 sizeof(*adb->deadentries) * adb->nentries);
2724 if (adb->entrylocks != NULL)
2725 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entrylocks,
2726 sizeof(*adb->entrylocks) * adb->nentries);
2727 if (adb->entry_sd != NULL)
2728 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entry_sd,
2729 sizeof(*adb->entry_sd) * adb->nentries);
2730 if (adb->entry_refcnt != NULL)
2731 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->entry_refcnt,
2732 sizeof(*adb->entry_refcnt) * adb->nentries);
2733 if (adb->names != NULL)
2734 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->names,
2735 sizeof(*adb->names) * adb->nnames);
2736 if (adb->deadnames != NULL)
2737 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->deadnames,
2738 sizeof(*adb->deadnames) * adb->nnames);
2739 if (adb->namelocks != NULL)
2740 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->namelocks,
2741 sizeof(*adb->namelocks) * adb->nnames);
2742 if (adb->name_sd != NULL)
2743 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->name_sd,
2744 sizeof(*adb->name_sd) * adb->nnames);
2745 if (adb->name_refcnt != NULL)
2746 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, adb->name_refcnt,
2747 sizeof(*adb->name_refcnt) * adb->nnames);
2748 if (adb->nmp != NULL)
2749 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->nmp);
2750 if (adb->nhmp != NULL)
2751 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->nhmp);
2752 if (adb->limp != NULL)
2753 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->limp);
2754 if (adb->emp != NULL)
2755 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->emp);
2756 if (adb->ahmp != NULL)
2757 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->ahmp);
2758 if (adb->aimp != NULL)
2759 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->aimp);
2760 if (adb->afmp != NULL)
2761 isc_mempool_destroy(&adb->afmp);
2762
2763 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->namescntlock);
2764 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->entriescntlock);
2765 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->overmemlock);
2766 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->reflock);
2767 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->mplock);
2768 isc_mutex_destroy(&adb->lock);
2769 if (adb->excl != NULL)
2770 isc_task_detach(&adb->excl);
2771 isc_mem_putanddetach(&adb->mctx, adb, sizeof(dns_adb_t));
2772
2773 return (result);
2774}
2775
2776void
2777dns_adb_attach(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adb_t **adbx) {
2778
2779 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
2780 REQUIRE(adbx != NULL && *adbx == NULL);
2781
2782 inc_adb_erefcnt(adb);
2783 *adbx = adb;
2784}
2785
2786void
2787dns_adb_detach(dns_adb_t **adbx) {
2788 dns_adb_t *adb;
2789 bool need_exit_check;
2790
2791 REQUIRE(adbx != NULL && DNS_ADB_VALID(*adbx));
2792
2793 adb = *adbx;
2794 *adbx = NULL;
2795
2796 INSIST(adb->erefcnt > 0);
2797
2798 LOCK(&adb->reflock);
2799 adb->erefcnt--;
2800 need_exit_check = (adb->erefcnt == 0 && adb->irefcnt == 0);
2801 UNLOCK(&adb->reflock);
2802
2803 if (need_exit_check) {
2804 LOCK(&adb->lock);
2805 INSIST(adb->shutting_down);
2806 check_exit(adb);
2807 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
2808 }
2809}
2810
2811void
2812dns_adb_whenshutdown(dns_adb_t *adb, isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t **eventp) {
2813 isc_task_t *tclone;
2814 isc_event_t *event;
2815 bool zeroirefcnt;
2816
2817 /*
2818 * Send '*eventp' to 'task' when 'adb' has shutdown.
2819 */
2820
2821 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
2822 REQUIRE(eventp != NULL);
2823
2824 event = *eventp;
2825 *eventp = NULL;
2826
2827 LOCK(&adb->lock);
2828 LOCK(&adb->reflock);
2829
2830 zeroirefcnt = (adb->irefcnt == 0);
2831
2832 if (adb->shutting_down && zeroirefcnt &&
2833 isc_mempool_getallocated(adb->ahmp) == 0) {
2834 /*
2835 * We're already shutdown. Send the event.
2836 */
2837 event->ev_sender = adb;
2838 isc_task_send(task, &event);
2839 } else {
2840 tclone = NULL;
2841 isc_task_attach(task, &tclone);
2842 event->ev_sender = tclone;
2843 ISC_LIST_APPEND(adb->whenshutdown, event, ev_link);
2844 }
2845
2846 UNLOCK(&adb->reflock);
2847 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
2848}
2849
2850static void
2851shutdown_stage2(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event) {
2852 dns_adb_t *adb;
2853
2854 UNUSED(task);
2855
2856 adb = event->ev_arg;
2857 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
2858
2859 LOCK(&adb->lock);
2860 INSIST(adb->shutting_down);
2861 adb->cevent_out = false;
2862 (void)shutdown_names(adb);
2863 (void)shutdown_entries(adb);
2864 if (dec_adb_irefcnt(adb))
2865 check_exit(adb);
2866 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
2867}
2868
2869void
2870dns_adb_shutdown(dns_adb_t *adb) {
2871 isc_event_t *event;
2872
2873 /*
2874 * Shutdown 'adb'.
2875 */
2876
2877 LOCK(&adb->lock);
2878
2879 if (!adb->shutting_down) {
2880 adb->shutting_down = true;
2881 isc_mem_setwater(adb->mctx, water, adb, 0, 0);
2882 /*
2883 * Isolate shutdown_names and shutdown_entries calls.
2884 */
2885 inc_adb_irefcnt(adb);
2886 ISC_EVENT_INIT(&adb->cevent, sizeof(adb->cevent), 0, NULL,
2887 DNS_EVENT_ADBCONTROL, shutdown_stage2, adb,
2888 adb, NULL, NULL);
2889 adb->cevent_out = true;
2890 event = &adb->cevent;
2891 isc_task_send(adb->task, &event);
2892 }
2893
2894 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
2895}
2896
2897isc_result_t
2898dns_adb_createfind(dns_adb_t *adb, isc_task_t *task, isc_taskaction_t action,
2899 void *arg, const dns_name_t *name, const dns_name_t *qname,
2900 dns_rdatatype_t qtype, unsigned int options,
2901 isc_stdtime_t now, dns_name_t *target,
2902 in_port_t port, unsigned int depth, isc_counter_t *qc,
2903 dns_adbfind_t **findp)
2904{
2905 dns_adbfind_t *find;
2906 dns_adbname_t *adbname;
2907 int bucket;
2908 bool want_event, start_at_zone, alias, have_address;
2909 isc_result_t result;
2910 unsigned int wanted_addresses;
2911 unsigned int wanted_fetches;
2912 unsigned int query_pending;
2913 char namebuf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
2914
2915 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
2916 if (task != NULL) {
2917 REQUIRE(action != NULL);
2918 }
2919 REQUIRE(name != NULL);
2920 REQUIRE(qname != NULL);
2921 REQUIRE(findp != NULL && *findp == NULL);
2922 REQUIRE(target == NULL || dns_name_hasbuffer(target));
2923
2924 REQUIRE((options & DNS_ADBFIND_ADDRESSMASK) != 0);
2925
2926 result = ISC_R_UNEXPECTED;
2927 POST(result);
2928 wanted_addresses = (options & DNS_ADBFIND_ADDRESSMASK);
2929 wanted_fetches = 0;
2930 query_pending = 0;
2931 want_event = false;
2932 start_at_zone = false;
2933 alias = false;
2934
2935 if (now == 0)
2936 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
2937
2938 /*
2939 * XXXMLG Move this comment somewhere else!
2940 *
2941 * Look up the name in our internal database.
2942 *
2943 * Possibilities: Note that these are not always exclusive.
2944 *
2945 * No name found. In this case, allocate a new name header and
2946 * an initial namehook or two. If any of these allocations
2947 * fail, clean up and return ISC_R_NOMEMORY.
2948 *
2949 * Name found, valid addresses present. Allocate one addrinfo
2950 * structure for each found and append it to the linked list
2951 * of addresses for this header.
2952 *
2953 * Name found, queries pending. In this case, if a task was
2954 * passed in, allocate a job id, attach it to the name's job
2955 * list and remember to tell the caller that there will be
2956 * more info coming later.
2957 */
2958
2959 find = new_adbfind(adb);
2960 if (find == NULL)
2961 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
2962
2963 find->port = port;
2964
2965 /*
2966 * Remember what types of addresses we are interested in.
2967 */
2968 find->options = options;
2969 find->flags |= wanted_addresses;
2970 if (FIND_WANTEVENT(find)) {
2971 REQUIRE(task != NULL);
2972 }
2973
2974 if (isc_log_wouldlog(dns_lctx, DEF_LEVEL))
2975 dns_name_format(name, namebuf, sizeof(namebuf));
2976 else
2977 namebuf[0] = 0;
2978
2979 /*
2980 * Try to see if we know anything about this name at all.
2981 */
2982 bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
2983 adbname = find_name_and_lock(adb, name, find->options, &bucket);
2984 INSIST(bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
2985 if (adb->name_sd[bucket]) {
2986 DP(DEF_LEVEL,
2987 "dns_adb_createfind: returning ISC_R_SHUTTINGDOWN");
2988 RUNTIME_CHECK(free_adbfind(adb, &find) == false);
2989 result = ISC_R_SHUTTINGDOWN;
2990 goto out;
2991 }
2992
2993 /*
2994 * Nothing found. Allocate a new adbname structure for this name.
2995 */
2996 if (adbname == NULL) {
2997 /*
2998 * See if there is any stale name at the end of list, and purge
2999 * it if so.
3000 */
3001 check_stale_name(adb, bucket, now);
3002
3003 adbname = new_adbname(adb, name);
3004 if (adbname == NULL) {
3005 RUNTIME_CHECK(free_adbfind(adb, &find) == false);
3006 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
3007 goto out;
3008 }
3009 link_name(adb, bucket, adbname);
3010 if (FIND_HINTOK(find))
3011 adbname->flags |= NAME_HINT_OK;
3012 if (FIND_GLUEOK(find))
3013 adbname->flags |= NAME_GLUE_OK;
3014 if (FIND_STARTATZONE(find))
3015 adbname->flags |= NAME_STARTATZONE;
3016 } else {
3017 /* Move this name forward in the LRU list */
3018 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(adb->names[bucket], adbname, plink);
3019 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(adb->names[bucket], adbname, plink);
3020 }
3021 adbname->last_used = now;
3022
3023 /*
3024 * Expire old entries, etc.
3025 */
3026 RUNTIME_CHECK(check_expire_namehooks(adbname, now) == false);
3027
3028 /*
3029 * Do we know that the name is an alias?
3030 */
3031 if (!EXPIRE_OK(adbname->expire_target, now)) {
3032 /*
3033 * Yes, it is.
3034 */
3035 DP(DEF_LEVEL,
3036 "dns_adb_createfind: name %s (%p) is an alias (cached)",
3037 namebuf, adbname);
3038 alias = true;
3039 goto post_copy;
3040 }
3041
3042 /*
3043 * Try to populate the name from the database and/or
3044 * start fetches. First try looking for an A record
3045 * in the database.
3046 */
3047 if (!NAME_HAS_V4(adbname) && EXPIRE_OK(adbname->expire_v4, now)
3048 && WANT_INET(wanted_addresses)) {
3049 result = dbfind_name(adbname, now, dns_rdatatype_a);
3050 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3051 DP(DEF_LEVEL,
3052 "dns_adb_createfind: found A for name %s (%p) in db",
3053 namebuf, adbname);
3054 goto v6;
3055 }
3056
3057 /*
3058 * Did we get a CNAME or DNAME?
3059 */
3060 if (result == DNS_R_ALIAS) {
3061 DP(DEF_LEVEL,
3062 "dns_adb_createfind: name %s (%p) is an alias",
3063 namebuf, adbname);
3064 alias = true;
3065 goto post_copy;
3066 }
3067
3068 /*
3069 * If the name doesn't exist at all, don't bother with
3070 * v6 queries; they won't work.
3071 *
3072 * If the name does exist but we didn't get our data, go
3073 * ahead and try AAAA.
3074 *
3075 * If the result is neither of these, try a fetch for A.
3076 */
3077 if (NXDOMAIN_RESULT(result))
3078 goto fetch;
3079 else if (NXRRSET_RESULT(result))
3080 goto v6;
3081
3082 if (!NAME_FETCH_V4(adbname))
3083 wanted_fetches |= DNS_ADBFIND_INET;
3084 }
3085
3086 v6:
3087 if (!NAME_HAS_V6(adbname) && EXPIRE_OK(adbname->expire_v6, now)
3088 && WANT_INET6(wanted_addresses)) {
3089 result = dbfind_name(adbname, now, dns_rdatatype_aaaa);
3090 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3091 DP(DEF_LEVEL,
3092 "dns_adb_createfind: found AAAA for name %s (%p)",
3093 namebuf, adbname);
3094 goto fetch;
3095 }
3096
3097 /*
3098 * Did we get a CNAME or DNAME?
3099 */
3100 if (result == DNS_R_ALIAS) {
3101 DP(DEF_LEVEL,
3102 "dns_adb_createfind: name %s (%p) is an alias",
3103 namebuf, adbname);
3104 alias = true;
3105 goto post_copy;
3106 }
3107
3108 /*
3109 * Listen to negative cache hints, and don't start
3110 * another query.
3111 */
3112 if (NCACHE_RESULT(result) || AUTH_NX(result))
3113 goto fetch;
3114
3115 if (!NAME_FETCH_V6(adbname))
3116 wanted_fetches |= DNS_ADBFIND_INET6;
3117 }
3118
3119 fetch:
3120 if ((WANT_INET(wanted_addresses) && NAME_HAS_V4(adbname)) ||
3121 (WANT_INET6(wanted_addresses) && NAME_HAS_V6(adbname)))
3122 have_address = true;
3123 else
3124 have_address = false;
3125 if (wanted_fetches != 0 &&
3126 ! (FIND_AVOIDFETCHES(find) && have_address)) {
3127 /*
3128 * We're missing at least one address family. Either the
3129 * caller hasn't instructed us to avoid fetches, or we don't
3130 * know anything about any of the address families that would
3131 * be acceptable so we have to launch fetches.
3132 */
3133
3134 if (FIND_STARTATZONE(find))
3135 start_at_zone = true;
3136
3137 /*
3138 * Start V4.
3139 */
3140 if (WANT_INET(wanted_fetches) &&
3141 fetch_name(adbname, start_at_zone, depth, qc,
3142 dns_rdatatype_a) == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3143 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "dns_adb_createfind: "
3144 "started A fetch for name %s (%p)",
3145 namebuf, adbname);
3146 }
3147
3148 /*
3149 * Start V6.
3150 */
3151 if (WANT_INET6(wanted_fetches) &&
3152 fetch_name(adbname, start_at_zone, depth, qc,
3153 dns_rdatatype_aaaa) == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3154 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "dns_adb_createfind: "
3155 "started AAAA fetch for name %s (%p)",
3156 namebuf, adbname);
3157 }
3158 }
3159
3160 /*
3161 * Run through the name and copy out the bits we are
3162 * interested in.
3163 */
3164 copy_namehook_lists(adb, find, qname, qtype, adbname, now);
3165
3166 post_copy:
3167 if (NAME_FETCH_V4(adbname))
3168 query_pending |= DNS_ADBFIND_INET;
3169 if (NAME_FETCH_V6(adbname))
3170 query_pending |= DNS_ADBFIND_INET6;
3171
3172 /*
3173 * Attach to the name's query list if there are queries
3174 * already running, and we have been asked to.
3175 */
3176 want_event = true;
3177 if (!FIND_WANTEVENT(find))
3178 want_event = false;
3179 if (FIND_WANTEMPTYEVENT(find) && FIND_HAS_ADDRS(find))
3180 want_event = false;
3181 if ((wanted_addresses & query_pending) == 0)
3182 want_event = false;
3183 if (alias)
3184 want_event = false;
3185 if (want_event) {
3186 find->adbname = adbname;
3187 find->name_bucket = bucket;
3188 bool empty = ISC_LIST_EMPTY(adbname->finds);
3189 ISC_LIST_APPEND(adbname->finds, find, plink);
3190 find->query_pending = (query_pending & wanted_addresses);
3191 find->flags &= ~DNS_ADBFIND_ADDRESSMASK;
3192 find->flags |= (find->query_pending & DNS_ADBFIND_ADDRESSMASK);
3193 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "createfind: attaching find %p to adbname "
3194 "%p %d",
3195 find, adbname, empty);
3196 } else {
3197 /*
3198 * Remove the flag so the caller knows there will never
3199 * be an event, and set internal flags to fake that
3200 * the event was sent and freed, so dns_adb_destroyfind() will
3201 * do the right thing.
3202 */
3203 find->query_pending = (query_pending & wanted_addresses);
3204 find->options &= ~DNS_ADBFIND_WANTEVENT;
3205 find->flags |= (FIND_EVENT_SENT | FIND_EVENT_FREED);
3206 find->flags &= ~DNS_ADBFIND_ADDRESSMASK;
3207 }
3208
3209 find->partial_result |= (adbname->partial_result & wanted_addresses);
3210 if (alias) {
3211 if (target != NULL) {
3212 result = dns_name_copy(&adbname->target, target, NULL);
3213 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3214 goto out;
3215 }
3216 result = DNS_R_ALIAS;
3217 } else
3218 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3219
3220 /*
3221 * Copy out error flags from the name structure into the find.
3222 */
3223 find->result_v4 = find_err_map[adbname->fetch_err];
3224 find->result_v6 = find_err_map[adbname->fetch6_err];
3225
3226 out:
3227 if (find != NULL) {
3228 *findp = find;
3229
3230 if (want_event) {
3231 isc_task_t *taskp;
3232
3233 INSIST((find->flags & DNS_ADBFIND_ADDRESSMASK) != 0);
3234 taskp = NULL;
3235 isc_task_attach(task, &taskp);
3236 find->event.ev_sender = taskp;
3237 find->event.ev_action = action;
3238 find->event.ev_arg = arg;
3239 }
3240 }
3241
3242 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
3243
3244 return (result);
3245}
3246
3247void
3248dns_adb_destroyfind(dns_adbfind_t **findp) {
3249 dns_adbfind_t *find;
3250 dns_adbentry_t *entry;
3251 dns_adbaddrinfo_t *ai;
3252 int bucket;
3253 dns_adb_t *adb;
3254 bool overmem;
3255
3256 REQUIRE(findp != NULL && DNS_ADBFIND_VALID(*findp));
3257 find = *findp;
3258 *findp = NULL;
3259
3260 LOCK(&find->lock);
3261
3262 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "dns_adb_destroyfind on find %p", find);
3263
3264 adb = find->adb;
3265 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
3266
3267 REQUIRE(FIND_EVENTFREED(find));
3268
3269 bucket = find->name_bucket;
3270 INSIST(bucket == DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
3271
3272 UNLOCK(&find->lock);
3273
3274 /*
3275 * The find doesn't exist on any list, and nothing is locked.
3276 * Return the find to the memory pool, and decrement the adb's
3277 * reference count.
3278 */
3279 overmem = isc_mem_isovermem(adb->mctx);
3280 ai = ISC_LIST_HEAD(find->list);
3281 while (ai != NULL) {
3282 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(find->list, ai, publink);
3283 entry = ai->entry;
3284 ai->entry = NULL;
3285 INSIST(DNS_ADBENTRY_VALID(entry));
3286 RUNTIME_CHECK(dec_entry_refcnt(adb, overmem, entry, true) ==
3287 false);
3288 free_adbaddrinfo(adb, &ai);
3289 ai = ISC_LIST_HEAD(find->list);
3290 }
3291
3292 /*
3293 * WARNING: The find is freed with the adb locked. This is done
3294 * to avoid a race condition where we free the find, some other
3295 * thread tests to see if it should be destroyed, detects it should
3296 * be, destroys it, and then we try to lock it for our check, but the
3297 * lock is destroyed.
3298 */
3299 LOCK(&adb->lock);
3300 if (free_adbfind(adb, &find))
3301 check_exit(adb);
3302 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
3303}
3304
3305void
3306dns_adb_cancelfind(dns_adbfind_t *find) {
3307 isc_event_t *ev;
3308 isc_task_t *task;
3309 dns_adb_t *adb;
3310 int bucket;
3311 int unlock_bucket;
3312
3313 LOCK(&find->lock);
3314
3315 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "dns_adb_cancelfind on find %p", find);
3316
3317 adb = find->adb;
3318 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
3319
3320 REQUIRE(!FIND_EVENTFREED(find));
3321 REQUIRE(FIND_WANTEVENT(find));
3322
3323 bucket = find->name_bucket;
3324 if (bucket == DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET)
3325 goto cleanup;
3326
3327 /*
3328 * We need to get the adbname's lock to unlink the find.
3329 */
3330 unlock_bucket = bucket;
3331 violate_locking_hierarchy(&find->lock, &adb->namelocks[unlock_bucket]);
3332 bucket = find->name_bucket;
3333 if (bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET) {
3334 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(find->adbname->finds, find, plink);
3335 find->adbname = NULL;
3336 find->name_bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
3337 }
3338 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[unlock_bucket]);
3339 bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
3340 POST(bucket);
3341
3342 cleanup:
3343
3344 if (!FIND_EVENTSENT(find)) {
3345 ev = &find->event;
3346 task = ev->ev_sender;
3347 ev->ev_sender = find;
3348 ev->ev_type = DNS_EVENT_ADBCANCELED;
3349 ev->ev_destroy = event_free;
3350 ev->ev_destroy_arg = find;
3351 find->result_v4 = ISC_R_CANCELED;
3352 find->result_v6 = ISC_R_CANCELED;
3353
3354 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "sending event %p to task %p for find %p",
3355 ev, task, find);
3356
3357 isc_task_sendanddetach(&task, (isc_event_t **)&ev);
3358 }
3359
3360 UNLOCK(&find->lock);
3361}
3362
3363void
3364dns_adb_dump(dns_adb_t *adb, FILE *f) {
3365 unsigned int i;
3366 isc_stdtime_t now;
3367
3368 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
3369 REQUIRE(f != NULL);
3370
3371 /*
3372 * Lock the adb itself, lock all the name buckets, then lock all
3373 * the entry buckets. This should put the adb into a state where
3374 * nothing can change, so we can iterate through everything and
3375 * print at our leisure.
3376 */
3377
3378 LOCK(&adb->lock);
3379 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
3380
3381 for (i = 0; i < adb->nnames; i++)
3382 RUNTIME_CHECK(cleanup_names(adb, i, now) == false);
3383 for (i = 0; i < adb->nentries; i++)
3384 RUNTIME_CHECK(cleanup_entries(adb, i, now) == false);
3385
3386 dump_adb(adb, f, false, now);
3387 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
3388}

3390static void
3391dump_ttl(FILE *f, const char *legend, isc_stdtime_t value, isc_stdtime_t now) {
3392 if (value == INT_MAX)
3393 return;
3394 fprintf(f, " [%s TTL %d]", legend, (int)(value - now));
3395}
3396
3397static void
3398dump_adb(dns_adb_t *adb, FILE *f, bool debug, isc_stdtime_t now) {
3399 unsigned int i;
3400 dns_adbname_t *name;
3401 dns_adbentry_t *entry;
3402
3403 fprintf(f, ";\n; Address database dump\n;\n");
3404 fprintf(f, "; [edns success/4096 timeout/1432 timeout/1232 timeout/"
3405 "512 timeout]\n");
3406 fprintf(f, "; [plain success/timeout]\n;\n");
3407 if (debug)
3408 fprintf(f, "; addr %p, erefcnt %u, irefcnt %u, finds out %u\n",
3409 adb, adb->erefcnt, adb->irefcnt,
3410 isc_mempool_getallocated(adb->nhmp));
3411
3412 for (i = 0; i < adb->nnames; i++)
3413 LOCK(&adb->namelocks[i]);
3414 for (i = 0; i < adb->nentries; i++)
3415 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[i]);
3416
3417 /*
3418 * Dump the names
3419 */
3420 for (i = 0; i < adb->nnames; i++) {
3421 name = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->names[i]);
3422 if (name == NULL)
3423 continue;
3424 if (debug)
3425 fprintf(f, "; bucket %u\n", i);
3426 for (;
3427 name != NULL;
3428 name = ISC_LIST_NEXT(name, plink))
3429 {
3430 if (debug)
3431 fprintf(f, "; name %p (flags %08x)\n",
3432 name, name->flags);
3433
3434 fprintf(f, "; ");
3435 print_dns_name(f, &name->name);
3436 if (dns_name_countlabels(&name->target) > 0) {
3437 fprintf(f, " alias ");
3438 print_dns_name(f, &name->target);
3439 }
3440
3441 dump_ttl(f, "v4", name->expire_v4, now);
3442 dump_ttl(f, "v6", name->expire_v6, now);
3443 dump_ttl(f, "target", name->expire_target, now);
3444
3445 fprintf(f, " [v4 %s] [v6 %s]",
3446 errnames[name->fetch_err],
3447 errnames[name->fetch6_err]);
3448
3449 fprintf(f, "\n");
3450
3451 print_namehook_list(f, "v4", adb,
3452 &name->v4, debug, now);
3453 print_namehook_list(f, "v6", adb,
3454 &name->v6, debug, now);
3455
3456 if (debug) {
3457 print_fetch_list(f, name);
3458 print_find_list(f, name);
3459 }
3460 }
3461 }
3462
3463 fprintf(f, ";\n; Unassociated entries\n;\n");
3464
3465 for (i = 0; i < adb->nentries; i++) {
3466 entry = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->entries[i]);
3467 while (entry != NULL) {
3468 if (entry->nh == 0)
3469 dump_entry(f, adb, entry, debug, now);
3470 entry = ISC_LIST_NEXT(entry, plink);
3471 }
3472 }
3473
3474 /*
3475 * Unlock everything
3476 */
3477 for (i = 0; i < adb->nentries; i++)
3478 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[i]);
3479 for (i = 0; i < adb->nnames; i++)
3480 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[i]);
3481}

3483static void
3484dump_entry(FILE *f, dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbentry_t *entry,
3485 bool debug, isc_stdtime_t now)
3486{
3487 char addrbuf[ISC_NETADDR_FORMATSIZE];
3488 char typebuf[DNS_RDATATYPE_FORMATSIZE];
3489 isc_netaddr_t netaddr;
3490 dns_adblameinfo_t *li;
3491
3492 isc_netaddr_fromsockaddr(&netaddr, &entry->sockaddr);
3493 isc_netaddr_format(&netaddr, addrbuf, sizeof(addrbuf));
3494
3495 if (debug)
3496 fprintf(f, ";\t%p: refcnt %u\n", entry, entry->refcnt);
3497
3498 fprintf(f, ";\t%s [srtt %u] [flags %08x] [edns %u/%u/%u/%u/%u] "
3499 "[plain %u/%u]", addrbuf, entry->srtt, entry->flags,
3500 entry->edns, entry->to4096, entry->to1432, entry->to1232,
3501 entry->to512, entry->plain, entry->plainto);
3502 if (entry->udpsize != 0U)
3503 fprintf(f, " [udpsize %u]", entry->udpsize);
3504 if (entry->cookie != NULL) {
3505 unsigned int i;
3506 fprintf(f, " [cookie=");
3507 for (i = 0; i < entry->cookielen; i++)
3508 fprintf(f, "%02x", entry->cookie[i]);
3509 fprintf(f, "]");
3510 }
3511 if (entry->expires != 0)
3512 fprintf(f, " [ttl %d]", (int)(entry->expires - now));
3513
3514 if (adb != NULL && adb->quota != 0 && adb->atr_freq != 0) {
3515 fprintf(f, " [atr %0.2f] [quota %u]",
3516 entry->atr, entry->quota);
3517 }
3518
3519 fprintf(f, "\n");
3520 for (li = ISC_LIST_HEAD(entry->lameinfo);
3521 li != NULL;
3522 li = ISC_LIST_NEXT(li, plink))
3523 {
3524 fprintf(f, ";\t\t");
3525 print_dns_name(f, &li->qname);
3526 dns_rdatatype_format(li->qtype, typebuf, sizeof(typebuf));
3527 fprintf(f, " %s [lame TTL %d]\n", typebuf,
3528 (int)(li->lame_timer - now));
3529 }
3530}

3532void
3533dns_adb_dumpfind(dns_adbfind_t *find, FILE *f) {
3534 char tmp[512];
3535 const char *tmpp;
3536 dns_adbaddrinfo_t *ai;
3537 isc_sockaddr_t *sa;
3538
3539 /*
3540 * Not used currently, in the API Just In Case we
3541 * want to dump out the name and/or entries too.
3542 */
3543
3544 LOCK(&find->lock);
3545
3546 fprintf(f, ";Find %p\n", find);
3547 fprintf(f, ";\tqpending %08x partial %08x options %08x flags %08x\n",
3548 find->query_pending, find->partial_result,
3549 find->options, find->flags);
3550 fprintf(f, ";\tname_bucket %d, name %p, event sender %p\n",
3551 find->name_bucket, find->adbname, find->event.ev_sender);
3552
3553 ai = ISC_LIST_HEAD(find->list);
3554 if (ai != NULL)
3555 fprintf(f, "\tAddresses:\n");
3556 while (ai != NULL) {
3557 sa = &ai->sockaddr;
3558 switch (sa->type.sa.sa_family) {
3559 case AF_INET:
3560 tmpp = inet_ntop(AF_INET, &sa->type.sin.sin_addr,
3561 tmp, sizeof(tmp));
3562 break;
3563 case AF_INET6:
3564 tmpp = inet_ntop(AF_INET6, &sa->type.sin6.sin6_addr,
3565 tmp, sizeof(tmp));
3566 break;
3567 default:
3568 tmpp = "UnkFamily";
3569 }
3570
3571 if (tmpp == NULL)
3572 tmpp = "BadAddress";
3573
3574 fprintf(f, "\t\tentry %p, flags %08x"
3575 " srtt %u addr %s\n",
3576 ai->entry, ai->flags, ai->srtt, tmpp);
3577
3578 ai = ISC_LIST_NEXT(ai, publink);
3579 }
3580
3581 UNLOCK(&find->lock);
3582}

3635
3636static isc_result_t
3637dbfind_name(dns_adbname_t *adbname, isc_stdtime_t now, dns_rdatatype_t rdtype)
3638{
3639 isc_result_t result;
3640 dns_rdataset_t rdataset;
3641 dns_adb_t *adb;
3642 dns_fixedname_t foundname;
3643 dns_name_t *fname;
3644
3645 INSIST(DNS_ADBNAME_VALID(adbname));
3646 adb = adbname->adb;
3647 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
3648 INSIST(rdtype == dns_rdatatype_a || rdtype == dns_rdatatype_aaaa);
3649
3650 fname = dns_fixedname_initname(&foundname);
3651 dns_rdataset_init(&rdataset);
3652
3653 if (rdtype == dns_rdatatype_a)
3654 adbname->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_UNEXPECTED;
3655 else
3656 adbname->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_UNEXPECTED;
3657
3658 /*
3659 * We need to specify whether to search static-stub zones (if
3660 * configured) depending on whether this is a "start at zone" lookup,
3661 * i.e., whether it's a "bailiwick" glue. If it's bailiwick (in which
3662 * case NAME_STARTATZONE is set) we need to stop the search at any
3663 * matching static-stub zone without looking into the cache to honor
3664 * the configuration on which server we should send queries to.
3665 */
3666 result = dns_view_find(adb->view, &adbname->name, rdtype, now,
3667 NAME_GLUEOK(adbname) ? DNS_DBFIND_GLUEOK : 0,
3668 NAME_HINTOK(adbname),
3669 ((adbname->flags & NAME_STARTATZONE) != 0),
3670 NULL, NULL, fname, &rdataset, NULL);
3671
3672 /* XXXVIX this switch statement is too sparse to gen a jump table. */
3673 switch (result) {
3674 case DNS_R_GLUE:
3675 case DNS_R_HINT:
3676 case ISC_R_SUCCESS:
3677 /*
3678 * Found in the database. Even if we can't copy out
3679 * any information, return success, or else a fetch
3680 * will be made, which will only make things worse.
3681 */
3682 if (rdtype == dns_rdatatype_a)
3683 adbname->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_SUCCESS;
3684 else
3685 adbname->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_SUCCESS;
3686 result = import_rdataset(adbname, &rdataset, now);
3687 break;
3688 case DNS_R_NXDOMAIN:
3689 case DNS_R_NXRRSET:
3690 /*
3691 * We're authoritative and the data doesn't exist.
3692 * Make up a negative cache entry so we don't ask again
3693 * for a while.
3694 *
3695 * XXXRTH What time should we use? I'm putting in 30 seconds
3696 * for now.
3697 */
3698 if (rdtype == dns_rdatatype_a) {
3699 adbname->expire_v4 = now + 30;
3700 DP(NCACHE_LEVEL,
3701 "adb name %p: Caching auth negative entry for A",
3702 adbname);
3703 if (result == DNS_R_NXDOMAIN)
3704 adbname->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_NXDOMAIN;
3705 else
3706 adbname->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_NXRRSET;
3707 } else {
3708 DP(NCACHE_LEVEL,
3709 "adb name %p: Caching auth negative entry for AAAA",
3710 adbname);
3711 adbname->expire_v6 = now + 30;
3712 if (result == DNS_R_NXDOMAIN)
3713 adbname->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_NXDOMAIN;
3714 else
3715 adbname->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_NXRRSET;
3716 }
3717 break;
3718 case DNS_R_NCACHENXDOMAIN:
3719 case DNS_R_NCACHENXRRSET:
3720 /*
3721 * We found a negative cache entry. Pull the TTL from it
3722 * so we won't ask again for a while.
3723 */
3724 rdataset.ttl = ttlclamp(rdataset.ttl);
3725 if (rdtype == dns_rdatatype_a) {
3726 adbname->expire_v4 = rdataset.ttl + now;
3727 if (result == DNS_R_NCACHENXDOMAIN)
3728 adbname->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_NXDOMAIN;
3729 else
3730 adbname->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_NXRRSET;
3731 DP(NCACHE_LEVEL,
3732 "adb name %p: Caching negative entry for A (ttl %u)",
3733 adbname, rdataset.ttl);
3734 } else {
3735 DP(NCACHE_LEVEL,
3736 "adb name %p: Caching negative entry for AAAA (ttl %u)",
3737 adbname, rdataset.ttl);
3738 adbname->expire_v6 = rdataset.ttl + now;
3739 if (result == DNS_R_NCACHENXDOMAIN)
3740 adbname->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_NXDOMAIN;
3741 else
3742 adbname->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_NXRRSET;
3743 }
3744 break;
3745 case DNS_R_CNAME:
3746 case DNS_R_DNAME:
3747 /*
3748 * Clear the hint and glue flags, so this will match
3749 * more often.
3750 */
3751 adbname->flags &= ~(DNS_ADBFIND_GLUEOK | DNS_ADBFIND_HINTOK);
3752
3753 rdataset.ttl = ttlclamp(rdataset.ttl);
3754 clean_target(adb, &adbname->target);
3755 adbname->expire_target = INT_MAX;
3756 result = set_target(adb, &adbname->name, fname, &rdataset,
3757 &adbname->target);
3758 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3759 result = DNS_R_ALIAS;
3760 DP(NCACHE_LEVEL,
3761 "adb name %p: caching alias target",
3762 adbname);
3763 adbname->expire_target = rdataset.ttl + now;
3764 }
3765 if (rdtype == dns_rdatatype_a)
3766 adbname->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_SUCCESS;
3767 else
3768 adbname->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_SUCCESS;
3769 break;
3770 }
3771
3772 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&rdataset))
3773 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&rdataset);
3774
3775 return (result);
3776}
3777
3778static void
3779fetch_callback(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *ev) {
3780 dns_fetchevent_t *dev;
3781 dns_adbname_t *name;
3782 dns_adb_t *adb;
3783 dns_adbfetch_t *fetch;
3784 int bucket;
3785 isc_eventtype_t ev_status;
3786 isc_stdtime_t now;
3787 isc_result_t result;
3788 unsigned int address_type;
3789 bool want_check_exit = false;
3790
3791 UNUSED(task);
3792
3793 INSIST(ev->ev_type == DNS_EVENT_FETCHDONE);
3794 dev = (dns_fetchevent_t *)ev;
3795 name = ev->ev_arg;
3796 INSIST(DNS_ADBNAME_VALID(name));
3797 adb = name->adb;
3798 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
3799
3800 bucket = name->lock_bucket;
3801 LOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
3802
3803 INSIST(NAME_FETCH_A(name) || NAME_FETCH_AAAA(name));
3804 address_type = 0;
3805 if (NAME_FETCH_A(name) && (name->fetch_a->fetch == dev->fetch)) {
3806 address_type = DNS_ADBFIND_INET;
3807 fetch = name->fetch_a;
3808 name->fetch_a = NULL;
3809 } else if (NAME_FETCH_AAAA(name)
3810 && (name->fetch_aaaa->fetch == dev->fetch)) {
3811 address_type = DNS_ADBFIND_INET6;
3812 fetch = name->fetch_aaaa;
3813 name->fetch_aaaa = NULL;
3814 } else
3815 fetch = NULL;
3816
3817 INSIST(address_type != 0 && fetch != NULL);
3818
3819 dns_resolver_destroyfetch(&fetch->fetch);
3820 dev->fetch = NULL;
3821
3822 ev_status = DNS_EVENT_ADBNOMOREADDRESSES;
3823
3824 /*
3825 * Cleanup things we don't care about.
3826 */
3827 if (dev->node != NULL)
3828 dns_db_detachnode(dev->db, &dev->node);
3829 if (dev->db != NULL)
3830 dns_db_detach(&dev->db);
3831
3832 /*
3833 * If this name is marked as dead, clean up, throwing away
3834 * potentially good data.
3835 */
3836 if (NAME_DEAD(name)) {
3837 free_adbfetch(adb, &fetch);
3838 isc_event_free(&ev);
3839
3840 want_check_exit = kill_name(&name, DNS_EVENT_ADBCANCELED);
3841
3842 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
3843
3844 if (want_check_exit) {
3845 LOCK(&adb->lock);
3846 check_exit(adb);
3847 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
3848 }
3849
3850 return;
3851 }
3852
3853 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
3854
3855 /*
3856 * If we got a negative cache response, remember it.
3857 */
3858 if (NCACHE_RESULT(dev->result)) {
3859 dev->rdataset->ttl = ttlclamp(dev->rdataset->ttl);
3860 if (address_type == DNS_ADBFIND_INET) {
3861 DP(NCACHE_LEVEL, "adb fetch name %p: "
3862 "caching negative entry for A (ttl %u)",
3863 name, dev->rdataset->ttl);
3864 name->expire_v4 = ISC_MIN(name->expire_v4,
3865 dev->rdataset->ttl + now);
3866 if (dev->result == DNS_R_NCACHENXDOMAIN)
3867 name->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_NXDOMAIN;
3868 else
3869 name->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_NXRRSET;
3870 inc_stats(adb, dns_resstatscounter_gluefetchv4fail);
3871 } else {
3872 DP(NCACHE_LEVEL, "adb fetch name %p: "
3873 "caching negative entry for AAAA (ttl %u)",
3874 name, dev->rdataset->ttl);
3875 name->expire_v6 = ISC_MIN(name->expire_v6,
3876 dev->rdataset->ttl + now);
3877 if (dev->result == DNS_R_NCACHENXDOMAIN)
3878 name->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_NXDOMAIN;
3879 else
3880 name->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_NXRRSET;
3881 inc_stats(adb, dns_resstatscounter_gluefetchv6fail);
3882 }
3883 goto out;
3884 }
3885
3886 /*
3887 * Handle CNAME/DNAME.
3888 */
3889 if (dev->result == DNS_R_CNAME || dev->result == DNS_R_DNAME) {
3890 dev->rdataset->ttl = ttlclamp(dev->rdataset->ttl);
3891 clean_target(adb, &name->target);
3892 name->expire_target = INT_MAX;
3893 result = set_target(adb, &name->name,
3894 dns_fixedname_name(&dev->foundname),
3895 dev->rdataset,
3896 &name->target);
3897 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3898 DP(NCACHE_LEVEL,
3899 "adb fetch name %p: caching alias target",
3900 name);
3901 name->expire_target = dev->rdataset->ttl + now;
3902 }
3903 goto check_result;
3904 }
3905
3906 /*
3907 * Did we get back junk? If so, and there are no more fetches
3908 * sitting out there, tell all the finds about it.
3909 */
3910 if (dev->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3911 char buf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
3912
3913 dns_name_format(&name->name, buf, sizeof(buf));
3914 DP(DEF_LEVEL, "adb: fetch of '%s' %s failed: %s",
3915 buf, address_type == DNS_ADBFIND_INET ? "A" : "AAAA",
3916 dns_result_totext(dev->result));
3917 /*
3918 * Don't record a failure unless this is the initial
3919 * fetch of a chain.
3920 */
3921 if (fetch->depth > 1)
3922 goto out;
3923 /* XXXMLG Don't pound on bad servers. */
3924 if (address_type == DNS_ADBFIND_INET) {
3925 name->expire_v4 = ISC_MIN(name->expire_v4, now + 10);
3926 name->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_FAILURE;
3927 inc_stats(adb, dns_resstatscounter_gluefetchv4fail);
3928 } else {
3929 name->expire_v6 = ISC_MIN(name->expire_v6, now + 10);
3930 name->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_FAILURE;
3931 inc_stats(adb, dns_resstatscounter_gluefetchv6fail);
3932 }
3933 goto out;
3934 }
3935
3936 /*
3937 * We got something potentially useful.
3938 */
3939 result = import_rdataset(name, &fetch->rdataset, now);
3940
3941 check_result:
3942 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3943 ev_status = DNS_EVENT_ADBMOREADDRESSES;
3944 if (address_type == DNS_ADBFIND_INET)
3945 name->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_SUCCESS;
3946 else
3947 name->fetch6_err = FIND_ERR_SUCCESS;
3948 }
3949
3950 out:
3951 free_adbfetch(adb, &fetch);
3952 isc_event_free(&ev);
3953
3954 clean_finds_at_name(name, ev_status, address_type);
3955
3956 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
3957}
3958
3959static isc_result_t
3960fetch_name(dns_adbname_t *adbname, bool start_at_zone,
3961 unsigned int depth, isc_counter_t *qc, dns_rdatatype_t type)
3962{
3963 isc_result_t result;
3964 dns_adbfetch_t *fetch = NULL;
3965 dns_adb_t *adb;
3966 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
3967 dns_name_t *name;
3968 dns_rdataset_t rdataset;
3969 dns_rdataset_t *nameservers;
3970 unsigned int options;
3971
3972 INSIST(DNS_ADBNAME_VALID(adbname));
3973 adb = adbname->adb;
3974 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
3975
3976 INSIST((type == dns_rdatatype_a && !NAME_FETCH_V4(adbname)) ||
3977 (type == dns_rdatatype_aaaa && !NAME_FETCH_V6(adbname)));
3978
3979 adbname->fetch_err = FIND_ERR_NOTFOUND;
3980
3981 name = NULL;
3982 nameservers = NULL;
3983 dns_rdataset_init(&rdataset);
3984
3985 options = DNS_FETCHOPT_NOVALIDATE;
3986 if (start_at_zone) {
3987 DP(ENTER_LEVEL,
3988 "fetch_name: starting at zone for name %p",
3989 adbname);
3990 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
3991 result = dns_view_findzonecut(adb->view, &adbname->name, name,
3992 NULL, 0, 0, true, false,
3993 &rdataset, NULL);
3994 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != DNS_R_HINT)
3995 goto cleanup;
3996 nameservers = &rdataset;
3997 options |= DNS_FETCHOPT_UNSHARED;
3998 }
3999
4000 fetch = new_adbfetch(adb);
4001 if (fetch == NULL) {
4002 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
4003 goto cleanup;
4004 }
4005 fetch->depth = depth;
4006
4007 /*
4008 * We're not minimizing this query, as nothing user-related should
4009 * be leaked here.
4010 * However, if we'd ever want to change it we'd have to modify
4011 * createfetch to find deepest cached name when we're providing
4012 * domain and nameservers.
4013 */
4014 result = dns_resolver_createfetch(adb->view->resolver, &adbname->name,
4015 type, name, nameservers, NULL,
4016 NULL, 0, options, depth, qc,
4017 adb->task, fetch_callback, adbname,
4018 &fetch->rdataset, NULL,
4019 &fetch->fetch);
4020 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
4021 DP(ENTER_LEVEL,
4022 "fetch_name: createfetch failed with %s",
4023 isc_result_totext(result));
4024 goto cleanup;
4025 }
4026
4027 if (type == dns_rdatatype_a) {
4028 adbname->fetch_a = fetch;
4029 inc_stats(adb, dns_resstatscounter_gluefetchv4);
4030 } else {
4031 adbname->fetch_aaaa = fetch;
4032 inc_stats(adb, dns_resstatscounter_gluefetchv6);
4033 }
4034 fetch = NULL; /* Keep us from cleaning this up below. */
4035
4036 cleanup:
4037 if (fetch != NULL)
4038 free_adbfetch(adb, &fetch);
4039 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&rdataset))
4040 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&rdataset);
4041
4042 return (result);
4043}

4045/*
4046 * XXXMLG Needs to take a find argument and an address info, no zone or adb,
4047 * since these can be extracted from the find itself.
4048 */
4049isc_result_t
4050dns_adb_marklame(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr,
4051 const dns_name_t *qname, dns_rdatatype_t qtype,
4052 isc_stdtime_t expire_time)
4053{
4054 dns_adblameinfo_t *li;
4055 int bucket;
4056 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
4057
4058 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4059 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4060 REQUIRE(qname != NULL);
4061
4062 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4063 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4064 li = ISC_LIST_HEAD(addr->entry->lameinfo);
4065 while (li != NULL &&
4066 (li->qtype != qtype || !dns_name_equal(qname, &li->qname)))
4067 li = ISC_LIST_NEXT(li, plink);
4068 if (li != NULL) {
4069 if (expire_time > li->lame_timer)
4070 li->lame_timer = expire_time;
4071 goto unlock;
4072 }
4073 li = new_adblameinfo(adb, qname, qtype);
4074 if (li == NULL) {
4075 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
4076 goto unlock;
4077 }
4078
4079 li->lame_timer = expire_time;
4080
4081 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(addr->entry->lameinfo, li, plink);
4082 unlock:
4083 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4084
4085 return (result);
4086}

4088void
4089dns_adb_adjustsrtt(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr,
4090 unsigned int rtt, unsigned int factor)
4091{
4092 int bucket;
4093 isc_stdtime_t now = 0;
4094
4095 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4096 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4097 REQUIRE(factor <= 10);
4098
4099 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4100 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4101
4102 if (addr->entry->expires == 0 || factor == DNS_ADB_RTTADJAGE)
4103 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
4104 adjustsrtt(addr, rtt, factor, now);
4105
4106 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4107}

4123
4124static void
4125adjustsrtt(dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr, unsigned int rtt, unsigned int factor,
4126 isc_stdtime_t now)
4127{
4128 uint64_t new_srtt;
4129
4130 if (factor == DNS_ADB_RTTADJAGE) {
4131 if (addr->entry->lastage != now) {
4132 new_srtt = addr->entry->srtt;
4133 new_srtt <<= 9;
4134 new_srtt -= addr->entry->srtt;
4135 new_srtt >>= 9;
4136 addr->entry->lastage = now;
4137 } else
4138 new_srtt = addr->entry->srtt;
4139 } else
4140 new_srtt = ((uint64_t)addr->entry->srtt / 10 * factor)
4141 + ((uint64_t)rtt / 10 * (10 - factor));
4142
4143 addr->entry->srtt = (unsigned int) new_srtt;
4144 addr->srtt = (unsigned int) new_srtt;
4145
4146 if (addr->entry->expires == 0)
4147 addr->entry->expires = now + ADB_ENTRY_WINDOW;
4148}

4150void
4151dns_adb_changeflags(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr,
4152 unsigned int bits, unsigned int mask)
4153{
4154 int bucket;
4155 isc_stdtime_t now;
4156
4157 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4158 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4159
4160 REQUIRE((bits & ENTRY_IS_DEAD) == 0);
4161 REQUIRE((mask & ENTRY_IS_DEAD) == 0);
4162
4163 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4164 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4165
4166 addr->entry->flags = (addr->entry->flags & ~mask) | (bits & mask);
4167 if (addr->entry->expires == 0) {
4168 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
4169 addr->entry->expires = now + ADB_ENTRY_WINDOW;
4170 }
4171
4172 /*
4173 * Note that we do not update the other bits in addr->flags with
4174 * the most recent values from addr->entry->flags.
4175 */
4176 addr->flags = (addr->flags & ~mask) | (bits & mask);
4177
4178 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4179}

4181/*
4182 * (10000 / ((10 + n) / 10)^(3/2)) for n in 0..99.
4183 * These will be used to make quota adjustments.
4184 */
4185static int quota_adj[] = {
4186 10000, 8668, 7607, 6747, 6037, 5443, 4941, 4512, 4141,
4187 3818, 3536, 3286, 3065, 2867, 2690, 2530, 2385, 2254,
4188 2134, 2025, 1925, 1832, 1747, 1668, 1595, 1527, 1464,
4189 1405, 1350, 1298, 1250, 1205, 1162, 1121, 1083, 1048,
4190 1014, 981, 922, 894, 868, 843, 820, 797, 775, 755,
4191 735, 716, 698, 680, 664, 648, 632, 618, 603, 590, 577,
4192 564, 552, 540, 529, 518, 507, 497, 487, 477, 468, 459,
4193 450, 442, 434, 426, 418, 411, 404, 397, 390, 383, 377,
4194 370, 364, 358, 353, 347, 342, 336, 331, 326, 321, 316,
4195 312, 307, 303, 298, 294, 290, 286, 282, 278
4196};
4197
4198#define QUOTA_ADJ_SIZE (sizeof(quota_adj)/sizeof(quota_adj[0]))
4199
4200/*
4201 * Caller must hold adbentry lock
4202 */
4203static void
4204maybe_adjust_quota(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr,
4205 bool timeout)
4206{
4207 double tr;
4208
4209 UNUSED(adb);
4210
4211 if (adb->quota == 0 || adb->atr_freq == 0)
4212 return;
4213
4214 if (timeout)
4215 addr->entry->timeouts++;
4216
4217 if (addr->entry->completed++ <= adb->atr_freq)
4218 return;
4219
4220 /*
4221 * Calculate an exponential rolling average of the timeout ratio
4222 *
4223 * XXX: Integer arithmetic might be better than floating point
4224 */
4225 tr = (double) addr->entry->timeouts / addr->entry->completed;
4226 addr->entry->timeouts = addr->entry->completed = 0;
4227 INSIST(addr->entry->atr >= 0.0);
4228 INSIST(addr->entry->atr <= 1.0);
4229 INSIST(adb->atr_discount >= 0.0);
4230 INSIST(adb->atr_discount <= 1.0);
4231 addr->entry->atr *= 1.0 - adb->atr_discount;
4232 addr->entry->atr += tr * adb->atr_discount;
4233 addr->entry->atr = ISC_CLAMP(addr->entry->atr, 0.0, 1.0);
4234
4235 if (addr->entry->atr < adb->atr_low && addr->entry->mode > 0) {
4236 addr->entry->quota = adb->quota *
4237 quota_adj[--addr->entry->mode] / 10000;
4238 log_quota(addr->entry, "atr %0.2f, quota increased to %u",
4239 addr->entry->atr, addr->entry->quota);
4240 } else if (addr->entry->atr > adb->atr_high &&
4241 addr->entry->mode < (QUOTA_ADJ_SIZE - 1)) {
4242 addr->entry->quota = adb->quota *
4243 quota_adj[++addr->entry->mode] / 10000;
4244 log_quota(addr->entry, "atr %0.2f, quota decreased to %u",
4245 addr->entry->atr, addr->entry->quota);
4246 }
4247
4248 /* Ensure we don't drop to zero */
4249 if (addr->entry->quota == 0)
4250 addr->entry->quota = 1;
4251}

4253#define EDNSTOS 3U
4254bool
4255dns_adb_noedns(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr) {
4256 int bucket;
4257 bool noedns = false;
4258
4259 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4260 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4261
4262 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4263 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4264
4265 if (addr->entry->edns == 0U &&
4266 (addr->entry->plain > EDNSTOS || addr->entry->to4096 > EDNSTOS)) {
4267 if (((addr->entry->plain + addr->entry->to4096) & 0x3f) != 0) {
4268 noedns = true;
4269 } else {
4270 /*
4271 * Increment plain so we don't get stuck.
4272 */
4273 addr->entry->plain++;
4274 if (addr->entry->plain == 0xff) {
4275 addr->entry->edns >>= 1;
4276 addr->entry->to4096 >>= 1;
4277 addr->entry->to1432 >>= 1;
4278 addr->entry->to1232 >>= 1;
4279 addr->entry->to512 >>= 1;
4280 addr->entry->plain >>= 1;
4281 addr->entry->plainto >>= 1;
4282 }
4283 }
4284 }
4285 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4286 return (noedns);
4287}

4314void
4315dns_adb_timeout(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr) {
4316 int bucket;
4317
4318 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4319 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4320
4321 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4322 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4323
4324 maybe_adjust_quota(adb, addr, true);
4325
4326 /*
4327 * If we have not had a successful query then clear all
4328 * edns timeout information.
4329 */
4330 if (addr->entry->edns == 0 && addr->entry->plain == 0) {
4331 addr->entry->to512 = 0;
4332 addr->entry->to1232 = 0;
4333 addr->entry->to1432 = 0;
4334 addr->entry->to4096 = 0;
4335 } else {
4336 addr->entry->to512 >>= 1;
4337 addr->entry->to1232 >>= 1;
4338 addr->entry->to1432 >>= 1;
4339 addr->entry->to4096 >>= 1;
4340 }
4341
4342 addr->entry->plainto++;
4343 if (addr->entry->plainto == 0xff) {
4344 addr->entry->edns >>= 1;
4345 addr->entry->plain >>= 1;
4346 addr->entry->plainto >>= 1;
4347 }
4348 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4349}

4351void
4352dns_adb_ednsto(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr, unsigned int size) {
4353 int bucket;
4354
4355 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4356 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4357
4358 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4359 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4360
4361 maybe_adjust_quota(adb, addr, true);
4362
4363 if (size <= 512U) {
4364 if (addr->entry->to512 <= EDNSTOS) {
4365 addr->entry->to512++;
4366 addr->entry->to1232++;
4367 addr->entry->to1432++;
4368 addr->entry->to4096++;
4369 }
4370 } else if (size <= 1232U) {
4371 if (addr->entry->to1232 <= EDNSTOS) {
4372 addr->entry->to1232++;
4373 addr->entry->to1432++;
4374 addr->entry->to4096++;
4375 }
4376 } else if (size <= 1432U) {
4377 if (addr->entry->to1432 <= EDNSTOS) {
4378 addr->entry->to1432++;
4379 addr->entry->to4096++;
4380 }
4381 } else {
4382 if (addr->entry->to4096 <= EDNSTOS)
4383 addr->entry->to4096++;
4384 }
4385
4386 if (addr->entry->to4096 == 0xff) {
4387 addr->entry->edns >>= 1;
4388 addr->entry->to4096 >>= 1;
4389 addr->entry->to1432 >>= 1;
4390 addr->entry->to1232 >>= 1;
4391 addr->entry->to512 >>= 1;
4392 addr->entry->plain >>= 1;
4393 addr->entry->plainto >>= 1;
4394 }
4395 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4396}

4398void
4399dns_adb_setudpsize(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr, unsigned int size) {
4400 int bucket;
4401
4402 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4403 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4404
4405 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4406 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4407 if (size < 512U)
4408 size = 512U;
4409 if (size > addr->entry->udpsize)
4410 addr->entry->udpsize = size;
4411
4412 maybe_adjust_quota(adb, addr, false);
4413
4414 addr->entry->edns++;
4415 if (addr->entry->edns == 0xff) {
4416 addr->entry->edns >>= 1;
4417 addr->entry->to4096 >>= 1;
4418 addr->entry->to1432 >>= 1;
4419 addr->entry->to1232 >>= 1;
4420 addr->entry->to512 >>= 1;
4421 addr->entry->plain >>= 1;
4422 addr->entry->plainto >>= 1;
4423 }
4424 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4425}

4443unsigned int
4444dns_adb_probesize(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr, int lookups) {
4445 int bucket;
4446 unsigned int size;
4447
4448 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4449 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4450
4451 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4452 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4453 if (addr->entry->to1232 > EDNSTOS || lookups >= 2)
4454 size = 512;
4455 else if (addr->entry->to1432 > EDNSTOS || lookups >= 1)
4456 size = 1232;
4457 else if (addr->entry->to4096 > EDNSTOS)
4458 size = 1432;
4459 else
4460 size = 4096;
4461 /*
4462 * Don't shrink probe size below what we have seen due to multiple
4463 * lookups.
4464 */
4465 if (lookups > 0 &&
4466 size < addr->entry->udpsize && addr->entry->udpsize < 4096)
4467 size = addr->entry->udpsize;
4468 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4469
4470 return (size);
4471}

4473void
4474dns_adb_setcookie(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr,
4475 const unsigned char *cookie, size_t len)
4476{
4477 int bucket;
4478
4479 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4480 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4481
4482 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4483 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4484
4485 if (addr->entry->cookie != NULL &&
4486 (cookie == NULL || len != addr->entry->cookielen)) {
4487 isc_mem_put(adb->mctx, addr->entry->cookie,
4488 addr->entry->cookielen);
4489 addr->entry->cookie = NULL;
4490 addr->entry->cookielen = 0;
4491 }
4492
4493 if (addr->entry->cookie == NULL && cookie != NULL && len != 0U) {
4494 addr->entry->cookie = isc_mem_get(adb->mctx, len);
4495 if (addr->entry->cookie != NULL)
4496 addr->entry->cookielen = (uint16_t)len;
4497 }
4498
4499 if (addr->entry->cookie != NULL)
4500 memmove(addr->entry->cookie, cookie, len);
4501 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4502}
4503
4504size_t
4505dns_adb_getcookie(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr,
4506 unsigned char *cookie, size_t len)
4507{
4508 int bucket;
4509
4510 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4511 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4512
4513 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4514 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4515 if (cookie != NULL && addr->entry->cookie != NULL &&
4516 len >= addr->entry->cookielen)
4517 {
4518 memmove(cookie, addr->entry->cookie, addr->entry->cookielen);
4519 len = addr->entry->cookielen;
4520 } else
4521 len = 0;
4522 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4523
4524 return (len);
4525}

4527isc_result_t
4528dns_adb_findaddrinfo(dns_adb_t *adb, const isc_sockaddr_t *sa,
4529 dns_adbaddrinfo_t **addrp, isc_stdtime_t now)
4530{
4531 int bucket;
4532 dns_adbentry_t *entry;
4533 dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr;
4534 isc_result_t result;
4535 in_port_t port;
4536
4537 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4538 REQUIRE(addrp != NULL && *addrp == NULL);
4539
4540 UNUSED(now);
4541
4542 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
4543 bucket = DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET;
4544 entry = find_entry_and_lock(adb, sa, &bucket, now);
4545 INSIST(bucket != DNS_ADB_INVALIDBUCKET);
4546 if (adb->entry_sd[bucket]) {
4547 result = ISC_R_SHUTTINGDOWN;
4548 goto unlock;
4549 }
4550 if (entry == NULL) {
4551 /*
4552 * We don't know anything about this address.
4553 */
4554 entry = new_adbentry(adb);
4555 if (entry == NULL) {
4556 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
4557 goto unlock;
4558 }
4559 entry->sockaddr = *sa;
4560 link_entry(adb, bucket, entry);
4561 DP(ENTER_LEVEL, "findaddrinfo: new entry %p", entry);
4562 } else
4563 DP(ENTER_LEVEL, "findaddrinfo: found entry %p", entry);
4564
4565 port = isc_sockaddr_getport(sa);
4566 addr = new_adbaddrinfo(adb, entry, port);
4567 if (addr == NULL) {
4568 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
4569 } else {
4570 inc_entry_refcnt(adb, entry, false);
4571 *addrp = addr;
4572 }
4573
4574 unlock:
4575 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4576
4577 return (result);
4578}

4580void
4581dns_adb_freeaddrinfo(dns_adb_t *adb, dns_adbaddrinfo_t **addrp) {
4582 dns_adbaddrinfo_t *addr;
4583 dns_adbentry_t *entry;
4584 int bucket;
4585 isc_stdtime_t now;
4586 bool want_check_exit = false;
4587 bool overmem;
4588
4589 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4590 REQUIRE(addrp != NULL);
4591 addr = *addrp;
4592 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBADDRINFO_VALID(addr));
4593 entry = addr->entry;
4594 REQUIRE(DNS_ADBENTRY_VALID(entry));
4595
4596 *addrp = NULL;
4597 overmem = isc_mem_isovermem(adb->mctx);
4598
4599 bucket = addr->entry->lock_bucket;
4600 LOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4601
4602 if (entry->expires == 0) {
4603 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
4604 entry->expires = now + ADB_ENTRY_WINDOW;
4605 }
4606
4607 want_check_exit = dec_entry_refcnt(adb, overmem, entry, false);
4608
4609 UNLOCK(&adb->entrylocks[bucket]);
4610
4611 addr->entry = NULL;
4612 free_adbaddrinfo(adb, &addr);
4613
4614 if (want_check_exit) {
4615 LOCK(&adb->lock);
4616 check_exit(adb);
4617 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
4618 }
4619}

4621void
4622dns_adb_flush(dns_adb_t *adb) {
4623 unsigned int i;
4624
4625 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4626
4627 LOCK(&adb->lock);
4628
4629 /*
4630 * Call our cleanup routines.
4631 */
4632 for (i = 0; i < adb->nnames; i++)
4633 RUNTIME_CHECK(cleanup_names(adb, i, INT_MAX) == false);
4634 for (i = 0; i < adb->nentries; i++)
4635 RUNTIME_CHECK(cleanup_entries(adb, i, INT_MAX) == false);
4636
4637#ifdef DUMP_ADB_AFTER_CLEANING
4638 dump_adb(adb, stdout, true, INT_MAX);
4639#endif
4640
4641 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
4642}

4644void
4645dns_adb_flushname(dns_adb_t *adb, const dns_name_t *name) {
4646 dns_adbname_t *adbname;
4647 dns_adbname_t *nextname;
4648 int bucket;
4649
4650 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4651 REQUIRE(name != NULL);
4652
4653 LOCK(&adb->lock);
4654 bucket = dns_name_hash(name, false) % adb->nnames;
4655 LOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
4656 adbname = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->names[bucket]);
4657 while (adbname != NULL) {
4658 nextname = ISC_LIST_NEXT(adbname, plink);
4659 if (!NAME_DEAD(adbname) &&
4660 dns_name_equal(name, &adbname->name)) {
4661 RUNTIME_CHECK(kill_name(&adbname,
4662 DNS_EVENT_ADBCANCELED) ==
4663 false);
4664 }
4665 adbname = nextname;
4666 }
4667 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[bucket]);
4668 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
4669}
4670
4671void
4672dns_adb_flushnames(dns_adb_t *adb, const dns_name_t *name) {
4673 dns_adbname_t *adbname, *nextname;
4674 unsigned int i;
4675
4676 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4677 REQUIRE(name != NULL);
4678
4679 LOCK(&adb->lock);
4680 for (i = 0; i < adb->nnames; i++) {
4681 LOCK(&adb->namelocks[i]);
4682 adbname = ISC_LIST_HEAD(adb->names[i]);
4683 while (adbname != NULL) {
4684 bool ret;
4685 nextname = ISC_LIST_NEXT(adbname, plink);
4686 if (!NAME_DEAD(adbname) &&
4687 dns_name_issubdomain(&adbname->name, name))
4688 {
4689 ret = kill_name(&adbname,
4690 DNS_EVENT_ADBCANCELED);
4691 RUNTIME_CHECK(ret == false);
4692 }
4693 adbname = nextname;
4694 }
4695 UNLOCK(&adb->namelocks[i]);
4696 }
4697 UNLOCK(&adb->lock);
4698}

4700static void
4701water(void *arg, int mark) {
4702 /*
4703 * We're going to change the way to handle overmem condition: use
4704 * isc_mem_isovermem() instead of storing the state via this callback,
4705 * since the latter way tends to cause race conditions.
4706 * To minimize the change, and in case we re-enable the callback
4707 * approach, however, keep this function at the moment.
4708 */
4709
4710 dns_adb_t *adb = arg;
4711 bool overmem = (mark == ISC_MEM_HIWATER);
4712
4713 REQUIRE(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4714
4715 DP(ISC_LOG_DEBUG(1),
4716 "adb reached %s water mark", overmem ? "high" : "low");
4717}

4719void
4720dns_adb_setadbsize(dns_adb_t *adb, size_t size) {
4721 size_t hiwater, lowater;
4722
4723 INSIST(DNS_ADB_VALID(adb));
4724
4725 if (size != 0U && size < DNS_ADB_MINADBSIZE)
4726 size = DNS_ADB_MINADBSIZE;
4727
4728 hiwater = size - (size >> 3); /* Approximately 7/8ths. */
4729 lowater = size - (size >> 2); /* Approximately 3/4ths. */
4730
4731 if (size == 0U || hiwater == 0U || lowater == 0U)
4732 isc_mem_setwater(adb->mctx, water, adb, 0, 0);
4733 else
4734 isc_mem_setwater(adb->mctx, water, adb, hiwater, lowater);
4735}
